00:12:19,656 --> 00:12:23,076
<font color="#FFFFFF">that allied troops
are moving to their support.</font>

208
00:12:24,036 --> 00:12:27,576
<font color="#FFFFFF">A hundred war planes
were seen over Brussels,</font>

209
00:12:27,664 --> 00:12:29,544
<font color="#FFFFFF">and it is now reported</font>

210
00:12:29,625 --> 00:12:32,005
<font color="#FFFFFF">that in the first raid over Brussels,</font>

211
00:12:32,085 --> 00:12:35,705
<font color="#FFFFFF">several hundred people
were killed and wounded,</font>

212
00:12:35,797 --> 00:12:38,427
<font color="#FFFFFF">and several buildings destroyed.</font>

213
00:12:40,219 --> 00:12:41,849
<font color="#FFFFFF">Five minutes ago,</font>

214
00:12:41,929 --> 00:12:43,929
<font color="#FFFFFF">the air ministry announced</font>

215
00:12:44,014 --> 00:12:46,474
<font color="#FFFFFF">that in the early hours of this morning...</font>

216
00:12:46,558 --> 00:12:49,938
<font color="#FFFFFF">Thank you, miss?</font>

217
00:12:50,437 --> 00:12:51,807
<font color="#FFFFFF">Layton.</font>

218
00:12:55,108 --> 00:12:56,648
<font color="#FFFFFF">- You're shaking.
- So are you.</font>

219
00:12:56,735 --> 00:13:00,155
<font color="#FFFFFF">You... you from excitement,
I from terror.</font>

220
00:13:00,239 --> 00:13:02,739
<font color="#FFFFFF">You've wanted this your entire adult life.</font>

221
00:13:02,824 --> 00:13:05,794
<font color="#FFFFFF">No. Since the nursery.
But do the public want me?</font>

222
00:13:05,869 --> 00:13:08,079
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's your own party to whom
you'll have to prove yourself.</font>

223
00:13:08,163 --> 00:13:11,423
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm getting the job only
because the ship is sinking.</font>

224
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:14,090
<font color="#FFFFFF">It-it's not a gift, it's revenge.</font>

225
00:13:14,169 --> 00:13:16,759
<font color="#FFFFFF">Let them see your true qualities,
your courage.</font>

226
00:13:16,839 --> 00:13:19,009
<font color="#FFFFFF">- My poor judgment.
- No, your lack of vanity.</font>

227
00:13:19,091 --> 00:13:21,091
<font color="#FFFFFF">- And my iron will.
- Your sense of humor.</font>

228
00:13:21,176 --> 00:13:22,506
<font color="#FFFFFF">Ho, ho, ho.</font>

229
00:13:23,929 --> 00:13:25,929
<font color="#FFFFFF">Now go.</font>

230
00:13:26,014 --> 00:13:27,394
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Go?
- Be...</font>

231
00:13:27,474 --> 00:13:28,524
<font color="#FFFFFF">Be what?</font>

232
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:30,020
<font color="#FFFFFF">Be yourself.</font>

233
00:13:32,938 --> 00:13:34,018
<font color="#FFFFFF">Myself?</font>

234
00:13:37,776 --> 00:13:40,566
<font color="#FFFFFF">Which self should I</font>

235
00:13:41,154 --> 00:13:42,494
<font color="#FFFFFF">be today?</font>

236
00:13:44,074 --> 00:13:46,664
<font color="#FFFFFF">One should have had power
when a young man.</font>

237
00:13:46,743 --> 00:13:48,243
<font color="#FFFFFF">When wits were sharp.</font>

238
00:13:48,328 --> 00:13:49,788
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sinews strong.</font>

239
00:13:49,872 --> 00:13:51,212
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, well.</font>

240
00:13:51,290 --> 00:13:53,040
<font color="#FFFFFF">Lead on, macduff.</font>

241
00:13:53,792 --> 00:13:56,092
<font color="#FFFFFF">When youth departs,</font>

242
00:13:56,587 --> 00:13:59,007
<font color="#FFFFFF">may wisdom prove enough.</font>

243
00:14:50,432 --> 00:14:53,312
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hardly seems like there's a war on at all.</font>

244
00:14:55,020 --> 00:14:57,900
<font color="#FFFFFF">Do you know I've never ridden a bus?</font>

245
00:14:58,732 --> 00:14:59,902
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sir?</font>

246
00:15:00,484 --> 00:15:02,244
<font color="#FFFFFF">I've never queued for bread.</font>

247
00:15:03,862 --> 00:15:06,112
<font color="#FFFFFF">I believe I can boil an egg.</font>

248
00:15:06,740 --> 00:15:08,660
<font color="#FFFFFF">But only because I've seen it done.</font>

249
00:15:10,869 --> 00:15:13,749
<font color="#FFFFFF">The only time I tried
riding the underground</font>

250
00:15:13,830 --> 00:15:15,670
<font color="#FFFFFF">was during the general strike.</font>

251
00:15:15,749 --> 00:15:18,959
<font color="#FFFFFF">Clemmie dropped me off
at south Kensington station.</font>

252
00:15:19,044 --> 00:15:21,304
<font color="#FFFFFF">I went down but got lost.</font>

253
00:15:21,880 --> 00:15:24,010
<font color="#FFFFFF">I came straight back up!</font>

254
00:15:24,091 --> 00:15:25,721
<font color="#FFFFFF">It was awful.</font>

255
00:15:27,511 --> 00:15:30,011
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why not halifax? I favor halifax.</font>

256
00:15:30,097 --> 00:15:31,427
<font color="#FFFFFF">I wanted halifax.</font>

257
00:15:31,849 --> 00:15:33,599
<font color="#FFFFFF">The lords wanted halifax.</font>

258
00:15:34,059 --> 00:15:36,979
<font color="#FFFFFF">Perhaps, halifax wanted halifax.</font>

259
00:15:37,271 --> 00:15:40,651
<font color="#FFFFFF">Then why have I been forced
to send for Churchill?</font>

260
00:15:41,441 --> 00:15:43,651
<font color="#FFFFFF">Because he is the only
member of our party</font>

261
00:15:43,735 --> 00:15:45,695
<font color="#FFFFFF">who has the support of the opposition.</font>

262
00:15:45,779 --> 00:15:49,159
<font color="#FFFFFF">His record is a litany of catastrophe.</font>

263
00:15:49,950 --> 00:15:52,410
<font color="#FFFFFF">Gallipoli, 25,000 dead,</font>

264
00:15:52,494 --> 00:15:55,084
<font color="#FFFFFF">the India policy, the Russian civil war,</font>

265
00:15:55,372 --> 00:15:56,752
<font color="#FFFFFF">the gold standard,</font>

266
00:15:58,292 --> 00:16:02,252
<font color="#FFFFFF">the abdication
and now this Norway adventure.</font>

267
00:16:02,337 --> 00:16:03,797
<font color="#FFFFFF">What's that, 1,800 men?</font>

268
00:16:03,881 --> 00:16:06,381
<font color="#FFFFFF">One aircraft carrier, two cruisers,</font>

269
00:16:06,466 --> 00:16:08,676
<font color="#FFFFFF">seven destroyers and a submarine.</font>

270
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:12,220
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Winston lacks judgment.
- He was right about Hitler.</font>

271
00:16:12,306 --> 00:16:15,136
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, even a stopped clock
is right twice a day.</font>

272
00:16:19,479 --> 00:16:22,189
<font color="#FFFFFF">First lord of the admiralty,
Mr. Winston Churchill.</font>

273
00:16:22,274 --> 00:16:23,324
<font color="#FFFFFF">Early.</font>

274
00:16:23,567 --> 00:16:24,567
<font color="#FFFFFF">Keen.</font>

275
00:16:28,655 --> 00:16:30,695
<font color="#FFFFFF">I accept your resignation,</font>

276
00:16:31,658 --> 00:16:33,948
<font color="#FFFFFF">but I want you to know how...</font>

277
00:16:34,828 --> 00:16:36,828
<font color="#FFFFFF">Cruelly I think you've been treated.</font>

278
00:16:38,332 --> 00:16:39,922
<font color="#FFFFFF">Thank you, your majesty.</font>

279
00:16:44,046 --> 00:16:45,546
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, this way, my lord.</font>

280
00:17:24,169 --> 00:17:25,339
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your majesty.</font>

281
00:17:25,420 --> 00:17:26,670
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mr. Churchill.</font>

282
00:17:27,589 --> 00:17:29,339
<font color="#FFFFFF">I believe you know</font>

283
00:17:31,009 --> 00:17:33,719
<font color="#FFFFFF">why I have asked you here today.</font>

284
00:17:33,804 --> 00:17:36,474
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sir, I simply cannot imagine why.</font>

285
00:17:41,061 --> 00:17:43,861
<font color="#FFFFFF">It is my duty to invite you</font>

286
00:17:43,939 --> 00:17:46,359
<font color="#FFFFFF">to take up the position of prime minister</font>

287
00:17:46,441 --> 00:17:48,321
<font color="#FFFFFF">of this United Kingdom.</font>

288
00:17:48,735 --> 00:17:50,815
<font color="#FFFFFF">Will you form a government?</font>

289
00:17:51,864 --> 00:17:53,034
<font color="#FFFFFF">I will.</font>

290
00:17:53,532 --> 00:17:54,572
<font color="#FFFFFF">Very well.</font>

291
00:18:10,090 --> 00:18:11,590
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, that was quite easy.</font>

292
00:18:12,968 --> 00:18:14,298
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes, it was.</font>

293
00:18:19,349 --> 00:18:23,019
<font color="#FFFFFF">I believe we are to meet regularly.</font>

294
00:18:23,896 --> 00:18:25,356
<font color="#FFFFFF">Once a week, I'm afraid.</font>

295
00:18:25,439 --> 00:18:26,479
<font color="#FFFFFF">How is...</font>

296
00:18:28,692 --> 00:18:30,192
<font color="#FFFFFF">How are you for mondays?</font>

297
00:18:31,111 --> 00:18:33,531
<font color="#FFFFFF">I shall endeavor to be available</font>

298
00:18:33,614 --> 00:18:35,414
<font color="#FFFFFF">- on mondays.
- 4:00?</font>

299
00:18:35,490 --> 00:18:37,160
<font color="#FFFFFF">I nap at 4:00.</font>

300
00:18:38,952 --> 00:18:41,162
<font color="#FFFFFF">Is that permissible?</font>

301
00:18:41,496 --> 00:18:43,326
<font color="#FFFFFF">No. But necessary.</font>

302
00:18:43,415 --> 00:18:44,535
<font color="#FFFFFF">I work late.</font>

303
00:18:44,625 --> 00:18:46,635
<font color="#FFFFFF">Then perhaps lunchtime.</font>

304
00:18:47,002 --> 00:18:48,342
<font color="#FFFFFF">Lunch?</font>

305
00:18:49,004 --> 00:18:50,344
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mondays?</font>

306
00:18:54,009 --> 00:18:55,839
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your majesty.</font>

307
00:18:55,928 --> 00:18:57,178
<font color="#FFFFFF">Prime minister.</font>

308
00:19:23,664 --> 00:19:25,714
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Can we get any closer?
- Mr. Churchill!</font>

309
00:19:26,708 --> 00:19:29,088
<font color="#FFFFFF">Good evening, gentlemen.</font>

310
00:19:29,169 --> 00:19:30,499
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mr. Churchill, welcome to number ten.</font>

311
00:19:30,587 --> 00:19:31,877
<font color="#FFFFFF">Thank you, sir.</font>

312
00:19:31,964 --> 00:19:33,674
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mr. Churchill, what's your agenda?</font>

313
00:19:33,757 --> 00:19:37,297
<font color="#FFFFFF">The agenda? A glass of pol Roger.</font>

314
00:19:37,386 --> 00:19:39,176
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Cheers.
- Over here, sir!</font>

315
00:19:39,263 --> 00:19:40,643
<font color="#FFFFFF">You'll-you'll have your pictures.</font>

316
00:19:40,722 --> 00:19:42,022
<font color="#FFFFFF">Prime minister.</font>

317
00:19:42,099 --> 00:19:43,309
<font color="#FFFFFF">Anthony.</font>

318
00:19:43,392 --> 00:19:45,142
<font color="#FFFFFF">How is the king?</font>

319
00:19:45,227 --> 00:19:46,597
<font color="#FFFFFF">Anxious.</font>

320
00:19:47,020 --> 00:19:50,270
<font color="#FFFFFF">He's never forgiven me for supporting</font>

321
00:19:50,691 --> 00:19:53,821
<font color="#FFFFFF">his brother's marriage to Wallis Simpson.</font>

322
00:19:53,902 --> 00:19:55,862
<font color="#FFFFFF">You only have to meet him once a week.</font>

323
00:19:55,946 --> 00:19:57,946
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, but that's like saying
you only have to have</font>

324
00:19:58,031 --> 00:20:00,081
<font color="#FFFFFF">your tooth pulled once a week.</font>

325
00:20:01,118 --> 00:20:03,038
<font color="#FFFFFF">Composition of your war cabinet.</font>

326
00:20:03,120 --> 00:20:04,750
<font color="#FFFFFF">Who should sit on it?</font>

327
00:20:04,830 --> 00:20:05,960
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yeah.</font>

328
00:20:06,039 --> 00:20:08,249
<font color="#FFFFFF">Chamberlain, of course.</font>

329
00:20:09,126 --> 00:20:12,296
<font color="#FFFFFF">The reverend holy fox.</font>

330
00:20:12,754 --> 00:20:14,014
<font color="#FFFFFF">Halifax.</font>

331
00:20:14,882 --> 00:20:16,682
<font color="#FFFFFF">Keeping your enemies close?</font>

332
00:20:16,758 --> 00:20:18,338
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, more than that.</font>

333
00:20:18,510 --> 00:20:21,510
<font color="#FFFFFF">Without them, the party
will have rid of me.</font>

334
00:20:21,597 --> 00:20:24,717
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, and that sheep
in sheep's clothing, attlee.</font>

335
00:20:25,559 --> 00:20:27,599
<font color="#FFFFFF">Come on, daddy. Everyone's waiting.</font>

336
00:20:27,686 --> 00:20:30,516
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes, I'll be there in a jiffy, my love.</font>

337
00:20:31,481 --> 00:20:33,731
<font color="#FFFFFF">I heard that before you were asked,</font>

338
00:20:33,817 --> 00:20:35,397
<font color="#FFFFFF">they offered it to lord halifax.</font>

339
00:20:35,485 --> 00:20:36,855
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, I doubt that.</font>

340
00:20:37,154 --> 00:20:39,824
<font color="#FFFFFF">Halifax would never turn it down.</font>

341
00:20:39,907 --> 00:20:42,487
<font color="#FFFFFF">He's the fourth son of an Earl.</font>

342
00:20:42,576 --> 00:20:44,366
<font color="#FFFFFF">Fourth sons turn nothing down.</font>

343
00:20:46,205 --> 00:20:49,295
<font color="#FFFFFF">I wish the position had come
your way in better times, sir.</font>

344
00:20:50,751 --> 00:20:52,291
<font color="#FFFFFF">You have an enormous task ahead of you.</font>

345
00:20:52,377 --> 00:20:54,667
<font color="#FFFFFF">I only hope it's not too late.</font>

346
00:20:55,214 --> 00:20:57,594
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm very much afraid it is.</font>

347
00:20:58,926 --> 00:21:01,136
<font color="#FFFFFF">But we can only do our best, hmm?</font>

348
00:21:01,345 --> 00:21:04,395
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Hip hip!
- Hurray!</font>

349
00:21:04,473 --> 00:21:05,643
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, heavens!</font>

350
00:21:05,724 --> 00:21:07,644
<font color="#FFFFFF">What a frightful sight.</font>

351
00:21:07,726 --> 00:21:09,766
<font color="#FFFFFF">- A toast.
- Yes, a speech.</font>

352
00:21:10,145 --> 00:21:11,895
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Yes.
- Mama.</font>

353
00:21:13,482 --> 00:21:14,692
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes.</font>

354
00:21:14,775 --> 00:21:16,995
<font color="#FFFFFF">My darling husband.</font>

355
00:21:17,069 --> 00:21:20,109
<font color="#FFFFFF">Some of you may not know that on the Eve</font>

356
00:21:20,197 --> 00:21:22,447
<font color="#FFFFFF">of our marriage, I got cold feet.</font>

357
00:21:22,533 --> 00:21:25,333
<font color="#FFFFFF">But as I'd already
called off two engagements</font>

358
00:21:25,410 --> 00:21:27,120
<font color="#FFFFFF">by the age of 21
and was in danger of gaining</font>

359
00:21:27,204 --> 00:21:28,544
<font color="#FFFFFF">a reputation for being a bolter</font>

360
00:21:28,622 --> 00:21:30,122
<font color="#FFFFFF">it would have been poor form</font>

361
00:21:30,207 --> 00:21:31,957
<font color="#FFFFFF">- to call off a third.
- Hear, hear.</font>

362
00:21:32,042 --> 00:21:33,382
<font color="#FFFFFF">Lucky for daddy.</font>

363
00:21:33,460 --> 00:21:35,710
<font color="#FFFFFF">But the real reason for my wintery feet</font>

364
00:21:35,796 --> 00:21:38,466
<font color="#FFFFFF">was that I knew, even then,</font>

365
00:21:39,091 --> 00:21:41,301
<font color="#FFFFFF">that his priority would be public life.</font>

366
00:21:42,803 --> 00:21:44,143
<font color="#FFFFFF">But it worried a young girl greatly,</font>

367
00:21:44,221 --> 00:21:46,641
<font color="#FFFFFF">this wretched thought
of eternally coming second.</font>

368
00:21:47,266 --> 00:21:48,926
<font color="#FFFFFF">But so it has proven to be.</font>

369
00:21:49,476 --> 00:21:52,596
<font color="#FFFFFF">And in due course, our children
would have to make their peace</font>

370
00:21:52,688 --> 00:21:54,058
<font color="#FFFFFF">with this same fact.</font>

371
00:21:56,900 --> 00:21:58,280
<font color="#FFFFFF">We all did, you see.</font>

372
00:21:58,861 --> 00:22:00,201
<font color="#FFFFFF">In our own way.</font>

373
00:22:03,365 --> 00:22:08,285
<font color="#FFFFFF">And now, today,
we are to receive our reward.</font>

374
00:22:09,288 --> 00:22:11,458
<font color="#FFFFFF">Proof that our small sacrifice</font>

375
00:22:11,540 --> 00:22:13,710
<font color="#FFFFFF">was for a far, far greater good.</font>

376
00:22:15,335 --> 00:22:17,295
<font color="#FFFFFF">I give you your father,</font>

377
00:22:18,213 --> 00:22:22,263
<font color="#FFFFFF">my beloved husband, the prime minister.</font>

378
00:22:23,177 --> 00:22:24,467
<font color="#FFFFFF">The prime minister.</font>

379
00:22:25,012 --> 00:22:26,642
<font color="#FFFFFF">Here's to,</font>

380
00:22:29,308 --> 00:22:31,728
<font color="#FFFFFF">to not buggering it up.</font>

381
00:22:31,810 --> 00:22:33,730
<font color="#FFFFFF">To not buggering it up.</font>

382
00:22:35,189 --> 00:22:37,019
<font color="#FFFFFF">Belgium was a ploy.</font>

383
00:22:37,524 --> 00:22:40,194
<font color="#FFFFFF">They punched through
the ardennes into France.</font>

384
00:22:40,277 --> 00:22:43,237
<font color="#FFFFFF">Crossed the meuse river in under 24 hours.</font>

385
00:22:43,322 --> 00:22:45,242
<font color="#FFFFFF">No one can cross the meuse in 24 hours.</font>

386
00:22:45,324 --> 00:22:46,744
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, apparently the Germans can.</font>

387
00:23:21,485 --> 00:23:23,115
<font color="#FFFFFF">Look to Chamberlain's handkerchief.</font>

388
00:23:23,195 --> 00:23:25,865
<font color="#FFFFFF">If he waves it
at the end of Churchill's speech,</font>

389
00:23:25,948 --> 00:23:27,368
<font color="#FFFFFF">we show approval.</font>

390
00:23:28,742 --> 00:23:31,332
<font color="#FFFFFF">If not, keep quiet.</font>

391
00:23:32,412 --> 00:23:34,462
<font color="#FFFFFF">The prime minister.</font>

392
00:23:44,967 --> 00:23:46,297
<font color="#FFFFFF">Here we go.</font>

393
00:23:49,179 --> 00:23:50,679
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mr. Speaker,</font>

394
00:23:51,682 --> 00:23:54,602
<font color="#FFFFFF">on Friday evening last,</font>

395
00:23:54,893 --> 00:23:58,103
<font color="#FFFFFF">I received his majesty's commission</font>

396
00:23:58,188 --> 00:24:01,018
<font color="#FFFFFF">to form a new administration.</font>

397
00:24:02,401 --> 00:24:05,321
<font color="#FFFFFF">It was the evident wish and will</font>

398
00:24:05,404 --> 00:24:08,414
<font color="#FFFFFF">of parliament and the nation</font>

399
00:24:08,490 --> 00:24:13,700
<font color="#FFFFFF">that this should be conceived
on the broadest possible basis.</font>

400
00:24:13,787 --> 00:24:16,537
<font color="#FFFFFF">And that it should include all parties.</font>

401
00:24:16,623 --> 00:24:18,083
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hear, hear.</font>

402
00:24:19,501 --> 00:24:22,381
<font color="#FFFFFF">A war cabinet has been convened.</font>

403
00:24:22,462 --> 00:24:26,222
<font color="#FFFFFF">No. Correction.</font>

404
00:24:26,300 --> 00:24:28,180
<font color="#FFFFFF">Has been formed.</font>

405
00:24:30,095 --> 00:24:31,095
<font color="#FFFFFF">"Formed."</font>

406
00:24:31,555 --> 00:24:35,735
<font color="#FFFFFF">A war cabinet has been formed
of five members</font>

407
00:24:35,809 --> 00:24:39,149
<font color="#FFFFFF">representing, with the opposition parties,</font>

408
00:24:39,730 --> 00:24:41,440
<font color="#FFFFFF">the unity of the nation.</font>

409
00:24:44,026 --> 00:24:45,316
<font color="#FFFFFF">Read.</font>

410
00:24:45,694 --> 00:24:47,114
<font color="#FFFFFF">"The three
party leaders have agreed</font>

411
00:24:47,196 --> 00:24:48,946
<font color="#FFFFFF">"to serve either in the war cabinet</font>

412
00:24:49,031 --> 00:24:51,621
<font color="#FFFFFF">"or in high executive office."</font>

413
00:24:51,700 --> 00:24:54,660
<font color="#FFFFFF">With this agreement in place,</font>

414
00:24:54,745 --> 00:24:56,915
<font color="#FFFFFF">I now invite the house</font>

415
00:24:56,997 --> 00:25:00,667
<font color="#FFFFFF">by the resolution which
stands in my name...</font>

416
00:25:01,084 --> 00:25:04,094
<font color="#FFFFFF">to record its approval</font>

417
00:25:04,588 --> 00:25:07,918
<font color="#FFFFFF">and to declare its confidence</font>

418
00:25:08,008 --> 00:25:09,338
<font color="#FFFFFF">in the new government.</font>

419
00:25:12,554 --> 00:25:13,684
<font color="#FFFFFF">Miss?</font>

420
00:25:14,473 --> 00:25:17,313
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm coming out in a state of nature.</font>

421
00:25:23,899 --> 00:25:25,319
<font color="#FFFFFF">It must be remembered</font>

422
00:25:26,068 --> 00:25:28,778
<font color="#FFFFFF">that we are in the preliminary stage</font>

423
00:25:28,862 --> 00:25:32,622
<font color="#FFFFFF">of one of the greatest battles in history.</font>

424
00:25:33,075 --> 00:25:37,625
<font color="#FFFFFF">And that many preparations
have to be made here at home.</font>

425
00:25:37,704 --> 00:25:39,084
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hear, hear.</font>

426
00:25:39,164 --> 00:25:41,544
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sir, I take up my task</font>

427
00:25:41,625 --> 00:25:44,635
<font color="#FFFFFF">with a buoyancy and hope,</font>

428
00:25:45,045 --> 00:25:48,545
<font color="#FFFFFF">and say to the house, as I have said</font>

429
00:25:48,632 --> 00:25:50,512
<font color="#FFFFFF">to those who have joined the government,</font>

430
00:25:51,009 --> 00:25:54,009
<font color="#FFFFFF">I have nothing to offer</font>

431
00:25:54,221 --> 00:25:58,731
<font color="#FFFFFF">but blood, toil, tears and sweat.</font>

432
00:26:00,894 --> 00:26:05,324
<font color="#FFFFFF">We have before us an ordeal
of the most grievous kind.</font>

433
00:26:06,233 --> 00:26:09,573
<font color="#FFFFFF">We have before us many, many long months</font>

434
00:26:09,653 --> 00:26:12,283
<font color="#FFFFFF">of struggle and of suffering.</font>

435
00:26:12,948 --> 00:26:16,118
<font color="#FFFFFF">You ask, "what is our policy?"</font>

436
00:26:17,369 --> 00:26:19,619
<font color="#FFFFFF">I say it is to wage war</font>

437
00:26:19,705 --> 00:26:23,335
<font color="#FFFFFF">by sea, land and air</font>

438
00:26:23,417 --> 00:26:25,167
<font color="#FFFFFF">with all our might</font>

439
00:26:25,627 --> 00:26:29,797
<font color="#FFFFFF">and with all the strength
that god can give us.</font>

440
00:26:30,465 --> 00:26:36,255
<font color="#FFFFFF">To wage war against a monstrous tyranny</font>

441
00:26:36,430 --> 00:26:39,850
<font color="#FFFFFF">never surpassed
in the dark and lamentable catalog</font>

442
00:26:39,933 --> 00:26:41,483
<font color="#FFFFFF">of human crime.</font>

443
00:26:41,560 --> 00:26:44,980
<font color="#FFFFFF">That is our policy.</font>

444
00:26:45,689 --> 00:26:48,479
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, you ask, "what is our aim?"</font>

445
00:26:49,193 --> 00:26:52,243
<font color="#FFFFFF">I can answer in one word.</font>

446
00:26:53,614 --> 00:26:54,994
<font color="#FFFFFF">Victory.</font>

447
00:26:55,073 --> 00:26:57,533
<font color="#FFFFFF">Victory at all costs.</font>

448
00:26:58,243 --> 00:27:01,373
<font color="#FFFFFF">Victory, in spite of all terror.</font>

449
00:27:01,455 --> 00:27:06,465
<font color="#FFFFFF">Victory, however long and hard
the road may be.</font>

450
00:27:07,044 --> 00:27:09,554
<font color="#FFFFFF">For without victory,</font>

451
00:27:10,005 --> 00:27:13,215
<font color="#FFFFFF">there can be no survival.</font>

452
00:27:29,691 --> 00:27:30,691
<font color="#FFFFFF">What's he doing?</font>

453
00:27:39,535 --> 00:27:40,875
<font color="#FFFFFF">Contempt.</font>

454
00:27:41,370 --> 00:27:43,290
<font color="#FFFFFF">We have to start somewhere.</font>

455
00:27:44,498 --> 00:27:45,538
<font color="#FFFFFF">Snap.</font>

456
00:27:54,216 --> 00:27:57,216
<font color="#FFFFFF">"Our policy is to wage war.</font>

457
00:27:57,636 --> 00:27:59,136
<font color="#FFFFFF">"At all costs.</font>

458
00:27:59,221 --> 00:28:00,891
<font color="#FFFFFF">"No survival."</font>

459
00:28:00,973 --> 00:28:02,183
<font color="#FFFFFF">Good god, he's incapable</font>

460
00:28:02,266 --> 00:28:04,886
<font color="#FFFFFF">of even pronouncing the word "peace,"</font>

461
00:28:05,143 --> 00:28:07,483
<font color="#FFFFFF">let alone entering into negotiations.</font>

462
00:28:08,564 --> 00:28:10,824
<font color="#FFFFFF">Awful, the thought that I shall never see</font>

463
00:28:10,899 --> 00:28:12,819
<font color="#FFFFFF">my country at peace again.</font>

464
00:28:16,446 --> 00:28:17,736
<font color="#FFFFFF">I have cancer.</font>

465
00:28:22,870 --> 00:28:23,910
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, Neville.</font>

466
00:28:29,751 --> 00:28:32,131
<font color="#FFFFFF">Winston must be removed from office.</font>

467
00:28:32,212 --> 00:28:34,512
<font color="#FFFFFF">If we can get him
to declare that he refuses</font>

468
00:28:34,590 --> 00:28:37,090
<font color="#FFFFFF">to even consider peace
negotiations with Germany,</font>

469
00:28:37,176 --> 00:28:40,096
<font color="#FFFFFF">you and I would perhaps
have clear grounds to resign.</font>

470
00:28:41,180 --> 00:28:43,560
<font color="#FFFFFF">That would force
a vote of no confidence.</font>

471
00:28:43,640 --> 00:28:45,480
<font color="#FFFFFF">The party couldn't countenance that.</font>

472
00:28:45,559 --> 00:28:47,309
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're the chairman, for heaven's sake.</font>

473
00:28:48,312 --> 00:28:49,352
<font color="#FFFFFF">He'd be finished.</font>

474
00:28:49,438 --> 00:28:52,068
<font color="#FFFFFF">And you would agree to be prime minister.</font>

475
00:28:52,816 --> 00:28:54,226
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well...</font>

476
00:28:55,485 --> 00:28:57,695
<font color="#FFFFFF">With Winston out of the way,
who can say?</font>

477
00:28:57,779 --> 00:29:00,029
<font color="#FFFFFF">But the important thing, Neville,</font>

478
00:29:00,115 --> 00:29:03,575
<font color="#FFFFFF">is that your policies
would be back on the table.</font>

479
00:29:03,660 --> 00:29:06,250
<font color="#FFFFFF">Peace and the protection of our nation.</font>

480
00:29:06,330 --> 00:29:07,750
<font color="#FFFFFF">On record.</font>

481
00:29:08,081 --> 00:29:09,171
<font color="#FFFFFF">I beg your pardon.</font>

482
00:29:09,249 --> 00:29:10,419
<font color="#FFFFFF">He must declare, on record,</font>

483
00:29:10,501 --> 00:29:13,881
<font color="#FFFFFF">his refusal to engage in peace talks.</font>

484
00:29:14,379 --> 00:29:16,379
<font color="#FFFFFF">We must have it in writing.</font>

485
00:29:56,088 --> 00:29:57,418
<font color="#FFFFFF">Thank you.</font>

486
00:29:59,341 --> 00:30:00,931
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Miss Layton.
- Morning.</font>

487
00:30:01,051 --> 00:30:02,391
<font color="#FFFFFF">Follow me.</font>

488
00:30:16,024 --> 00:30:17,154
<font color="#FFFFFF">Morning.</font>

489
00:30:17,234 --> 00:30:18,784
<font color="#FFFFFF">Thank you, sir.</font>

490
00:30:20,112 --> 00:30:21,492
<font color="#FFFFFF">Thank you, ma'am.</font>

491
00:30:23,574 --> 00:30:25,204
<font color="#FFFFFF">What goes on down here?</font>

492
00:30:25,284 --> 00:30:28,204
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's need-to-know, and you don't.</font>

493
00:30:28,287 --> 00:30:30,657
<font color="#FFFFFF">- The lavatory?
- For the pm's use only.</font>

494
00:30:31,623 --> 00:30:32,753
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sleeping quarters,</font>

495
00:30:32,833 --> 00:30:34,833
<font color="#FFFFFF">for when you miss the last train.</font>

496
00:30:36,545 --> 00:30:37,555
<font color="#FFFFFF">Ma'am.</font>

497
00:30:39,923 --> 00:30:41,803
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's the map room.</font>

498
00:30:42,426 --> 00:30:44,756
<font color="#FFFFFF">- No women allowed.
- What department's this?</font>

499
00:30:44,845 --> 00:30:47,015
<font color="#FFFFFF">Indiscretion in conversation
or any other form,</font>

500
00:30:47,097 --> 00:30:49,057
<font color="#FFFFFF">within or without these rooms
regarding what happens here,</font>

501
00:30:49,141 --> 00:30:51,771
<font color="#FFFFFF">is a statutory offense punishable by up to</font>

502
00:30:51,852 --> 00:30:54,192
<font color="#FFFFFF">two years imprisonment with hard labor.</font>

503
00:30:54,855 --> 00:30:56,115
<font color="#FFFFFF">Clear?</font>

504
00:30:56,190 --> 00:30:57,360
<font color="#FFFFFF">Crystal.</font>

505
00:30:57,441 --> 00:30:58,481
<font color="#FFFFFF">Good.</font>

506
00:30:59,902 --> 00:31:01,572
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's the war cabinet room.</font>

507
00:31:01,987 --> 00:31:03,147
<font color="#FFFFFF">Never.</font>

508
00:31:04,865 --> 00:31:07,665
<font color="#FFFFFF">I don't mean to be rough on you, but</font>

509
00:31:08,243 --> 00:31:09,873
<font color="#FFFFFF">them's the rules.</font>

510
00:31:11,205 --> 00:31:13,255
<font color="#FFFFFF">This is the typists' pool.</font>

511
00:31:13,373 --> 00:31:15,503
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Good morning, sir.
- Ladies.</font>

512
00:31:17,294 --> 00:31:18,844
<font color="#FFFFFF">And here's you.</font>

513
00:31:26,678 --> 00:31:29,098
<font color="#FFFFFF">Belgium and Holland may fall at any hour.</font>

514
00:31:29,181 --> 00:31:30,561
<font color="#FFFFFF">And the French?</font>

515
00:31:30,641 --> 00:31:32,061
<font color="#FFFFFF">The entire French ninth army,</font>

516
00:31:32,142 --> 00:31:34,732
<font color="#FFFFFF">some 200,000 men, have capitulated.</font>

517
00:31:35,437 --> 00:31:36,437
<font color="#FFFFFF">All of them?</font>

518
00:31:36,522 --> 00:31:37,692
<font color="#FFFFFF">Capitulated.</font>

519
00:31:37,773 --> 00:31:39,693
<font color="#FFFFFF">Deserted. It was a rout.</font>

520
00:31:39,775 --> 00:31:42,655
<font color="#FFFFFF">All our land forces,
roughly 300,000 men,</font>

521
00:31:42,736 --> 00:31:44,066
<font color="#FFFFFF">are now in full retreat.</font>

522
00:31:44,530 --> 00:31:46,610
<font color="#FFFFFF">Air cover? For our troops?</font>

523
00:31:46,698 --> 00:31:48,578
<font color="#FFFFFF">The luftwaffe control the skies.</font>

524
00:31:48,659 --> 00:31:51,119
<font color="#FFFFFF">We simply don't have enough
planes to challenge them.</font>

525
00:31:51,203 --> 00:31:53,413
<font color="#FFFFFF">In fact, I strongly
recommend we stop sending</font>

526
00:31:53,497 --> 00:31:56,367
<font color="#FFFFFF">our precious fighter planes
to be wasted in France.</font>

527
00:31:56,458 --> 00:31:58,288
<font color="#FFFFFF">Save them for our own defense.</font>

528
00:31:58,502 --> 00:32:01,342
<font color="#FFFFFF">And our Navy sits idle,</font>

529
00:32:01,421 --> 00:32:03,591
<font color="#FFFFFF">neutralized, useless.</font>

530
00:32:03,674 --> 00:32:06,134
<font color="#FFFFFF">Our fleets no sooner
come within their range</font>

531
00:32:06,218 --> 00:32:08,178
<font color="#FFFFFF">than we come under blistering air attack.</font>

532
00:32:08,262 --> 00:32:12,312
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, their speed is devastating.</font>

533
00:32:12,391 --> 00:32:15,641
<font color="#FFFFFF">Panzer tanks moving rapidly westward
through the center.</font>

534
00:32:15,727 --> 00:32:19,807
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, they will have to pause
for fuel supplies.</font>

535
00:32:19,898 --> 00:32:21,478
<font color="#FFFFFF">This is not the last war, sir.</font>

536
00:32:21,567 --> 00:32:24,487
<font color="#FFFFFF">Their tanks can stop for fuel
at a petrol station.</font>

537
00:32:25,696 --> 00:32:27,156
<font color="#FFFFFF">Petrol station?</font>

538
00:32:27,239 --> 00:32:29,739
<font color="#FFFFFF">The road to Paris now lies open.</font>

539
00:32:29,825 --> 00:32:32,165
<font color="#FFFFFF">Seven million refugees are on the move.</font>

540
00:32:33,745 --> 00:32:35,575
<font color="#FFFFFF">Collectively, we are looking
at the collapse</font>

541
00:32:35,664 --> 00:32:37,964
<font color="#FFFFFF">of western Europe in the next few days.</font>

542
00:32:38,041 --> 00:32:40,421
<font color="#FFFFFF">Should the public be told?</font>

543
00:32:46,717 --> 00:32:48,087
<font color="#FFFFFF">Not yet.</font>

544
00:32:48,844 --> 00:32:51,474
<font color="#FFFFFF">First, we must rouse our old friends</font>

545
00:32:51,555 --> 00:32:54,145
<font color="#FFFFFF">to a heroic resistance.</font>

546
00:32:55,142 --> 00:32:57,942
<font color="#FFFFFF">France must be saved.</font>

547
00:34:03,168 --> 00:34:04,588
<font color="#FFFFFF">Premier.</font>

548
00:34:30,988 --> 00:34:33,818
<font color="#FFFFFF">Perhaps, in English, prime minister.</font>

549
00:34:34,241 --> 00:34:35,451
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well...</font>

550
00:34:35,534 --> 00:34:40,044
<font color="#FFFFFF">We have survived crises before,</font>

551
00:34:40,122 --> 00:34:43,962
<font color="#FFFFFF">and I am... I am confident
we will survive this one.</font>

552
00:34:44,042 --> 00:34:47,422
<font color="#FFFFFF">Tell me how you plan to counter-attack.</font>

553
00:34:49,298 --> 00:34:50,588
<font color="#FFFFFF">There is no plan.</font>

554
00:34:52,342 --> 00:34:54,512
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well...</font>

555
00:34:54,636 --> 00:34:56,546
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, you must counter-attack.</font>

556
00:34:57,181 --> 00:34:59,181
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, you must.</font>

557
00:35:07,941 --> 00:35:11,741
<font color="#FFFFFF">I do not
believe that this,</font>

558
00:35:12,112 --> 00:35:15,372
<font color="#FFFFFF">panzer breakthrough is a real invasion.</font>

559
00:35:15,449 --> 00:35:17,409
<font color="#FFFFFF">Not a real invasion?</font>

560
00:35:17,492 --> 00:35:20,752
<font color="#FFFFFF">No. As long as their tank crews
are not supported</font>

561
00:35:20,829 --> 00:35:23,619
<font color="#FFFFFF">by infantry units, they are</font>

562
00:35:24,249 --> 00:35:27,749
<font color="#FFFFFF">merely little flags stuck on a map.</font>

563
00:35:27,836 --> 00:35:31,166
<font color="#FFFFFF">Because the tank crews
cannot support themselves.</font>

564
00:35:31,256 --> 00:35:33,426
<font color="#FFFFFF">No. I refuse to see,</font>

565
00:35:33,509 --> 00:35:36,799
<font color="#FFFFFF">in this spectacular raid
of the German tank,</font>

566
00:35:37,095 --> 00:35:39,005
<font color="#FFFFFF">a real invasion.</font>

567
00:35:51,485 --> 00:35:52,995
<font color="#FFFFFF">He's an actor,</font>

568
00:35:53,070 --> 00:35:55,200
<font color="#FFFFFF">in love with the sound of his own voice.</font>

569
00:35:55,280 --> 00:35:57,320
<font color="#FFFFFF">I love to listen to him.</font>

570
00:35:57,783 --> 00:35:59,873
<font color="#FFFFFF">But we must never take his advice.</font>

571
00:36:00,285 --> 00:36:02,195
<font color="#FFFFFF">Has a hundred ideas a day.</font>

572
00:36:02,287 --> 00:36:03,747
<font color="#FFFFFF">Four of them are good,</font>

573
00:36:04,122 --> 00:36:06,082
<font color="#FFFFFF">the other 96 downright dangerous.</font>

574
00:36:06,166 --> 00:36:10,086
<font color="#FFFFFF">His father was the same.
Great orator, but...</font>

575
00:36:10,170 --> 00:36:11,960
<font color="#FFFFFF">Until he lost his mind to syphilis.</font>

576
00:36:12,381 --> 00:36:15,471
<font color="#FFFFFF">How nations suffer
for the sins of their fathers.</font>

577
00:36:15,551 --> 00:36:16,761
<font color="#FFFFFF">My opinion?</font>

578
00:36:16,844 --> 00:36:19,394
<font color="#FFFFFF">At this critical juncture for the empire,</font>

579
00:36:20,305 --> 00:36:23,015
<font color="#FFFFFF">we have a drunkard at the wheel.</font>

580
00:36:23,392 --> 00:36:25,482
<font color="#FFFFFF">Wakes with a scotch,</font>

581
00:36:25,769 --> 00:36:28,479
<font color="#FFFFFF">bottle of champagne for lunch,</font>

582
00:36:28,564 --> 00:36:30,154
<font color="#FFFFFF">another one at dinner.</font>

583
00:36:30,983 --> 00:36:33,783
<font color="#FFFFFF">Brandy and port until the wee hours.</font>

584
00:36:34,528 --> 00:36:36,698
<font color="#FFFFFF">I wouldn't let him borrow my bicycle.</font>

585
00:36:36,780 --> 00:36:39,620
<font color="#FFFFFF">He's a conservative
who defects to the liberals,</font>

586
00:36:39,700 --> 00:36:42,240
<font color="#FFFFFF">lobs grenades at us for ten years,</font>

587
00:36:42,327 --> 00:36:45,957
<font color="#FFFFFF">then flops conservative again
as it bloody suits him.</font>

588
00:36:46,039 --> 00:36:49,169
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sorry, but he stands for one thing.</font>

589
00:36:49,334 --> 00:36:50,504
<font color="#FFFFFF">Himself.</font>

590
00:36:51,503 --> 00:36:53,673
<font color="#FFFFFF">We may have to replace him, bertie.</font>

591
00:36:55,132 --> 00:36:56,422
<font color="#FFFFFF">Replace him?</font>

592
00:36:57,050 --> 00:36:58,930
<font color="#FFFFFF">We must strive for peace</font>

593
00:36:59,469 --> 00:37:01,599
<font color="#FFFFFF">so that every
son and daughter of this land</font>

594
00:37:01,680 --> 00:37:03,260
<font color="#FFFFFF">can emerge from this crisis</font>

595
00:37:03,348 --> 00:37:05,558
<font color="#FFFFFF">with something recognizable as home.</font>

596
00:37:07,352 --> 00:37:09,602
<font color="#FFFFFF">Spoken like a true prime minister.</font>

597
00:37:24,745 --> 00:37:26,915
<font color="#FFFFFF">"V for victory."</font>

598
00:37:28,582 --> 00:37:31,212
<font color="#FFFFFF">You need to reply to the lord privy seal.</font>

599
00:37:34,546 --> 00:37:38,466
<font color="#FFFFFF">Tell the lord privy seal
I am sealed in the privy.</font>

600
00:37:39,676 --> 00:37:42,796
<font color="#FFFFFF">And I can only deal
with one shit at a time.</font>

601
00:37:50,145 --> 00:37:54,145
<font color="#FFFFFF">The broadcast is tonight,
so don't spare me, Anthony.</font>

602
00:37:54,525 --> 00:37:55,785
<font color="#FFFFFF">Be frank.</font>

603
00:38:04,076 --> 00:38:05,696
<font color="#FFFFFF">I don't think so.</font>

604
00:38:06,036 --> 00:38:07,946
<font color="#FFFFFF">You don't think so what?</font>

605
00:38:08,247 --> 00:38:10,497
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're suggesting we're somehow winning.</font>

606
00:38:10,916 --> 00:38:12,166
<font color="#FFFFFF">We're not.</font>

607
00:38:13,001 --> 00:38:16,631
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, but it will inspire them.</font>

608
00:38:17,130 --> 00:38:19,170
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Winston, I know...
- Anthony, Anthony.</font>

609
00:38:19,258 --> 00:38:22,638
<font color="#FFFFFF">I am going to imbue them with a...</font>

610
00:38:22,719 --> 00:38:26,889
<font color="#FFFFFF">A spirit of feeling
they don't yet know they have.</font>

611
00:38:26,974 --> 00:38:28,314
<font color="#FFFFFF">You asked my opinion.</font>

612
00:38:29,518 --> 00:38:31,268
<font color="#FFFFFF">I caution against it.</font>

613
00:38:33,814 --> 00:38:34,814
<font color="#FFFFFF">Cicero.</font>

614
00:38:37,359 --> 00:38:39,069
<font color="#FFFFFF">Cicero!</font>

615
00:38:41,405 --> 00:38:45,785
<font color="#FFFFFF">"If fortune is adverse..." Something,</font>

616
00:38:45,868 --> 00:38:48,198
<font color="#FFFFFF">something, something.</font>

617
00:38:53,917 --> 00:38:55,207
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well...</font>

618
00:38:55,711 --> 00:38:58,801
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, it's not there. I left it there.</font>

619
00:38:58,881 --> 00:39:00,471
<font color="#FFFFFF">Clemmie!</font>

620
00:39:01,091 --> 00:39:02,381
<font color="#FFFFFF">Cat!</font>

621
00:39:02,467 --> 00:39:03,637
<font color="#FFFFFF">Clemmie!</font>

622
00:39:03,719 --> 00:39:04,929
<font color="#FFFFFF">We cannot pay our bills.</font>

623
00:39:05,012 --> 00:39:07,602
<font color="#FFFFFF">My copy of Cicero.</font>

624
00:39:07,973 --> 00:39:09,393
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Did-did you shelve it?
- Did you hear what I said?</font>

625
00:39:09,474 --> 00:39:10,814
<font color="#FFFFFF">- What was that?
- We're broke.</font>

626
00:39:12,936 --> 00:39:14,556
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, um... out! Out.</font>

627
00:39:14,646 --> 00:39:16,396
<font color="#FFFFFF">Come on. Everybody out.</font>

628
00:39:17,441 --> 00:39:19,111
<font color="#FFFFFF">I dare not write another check.</font>

629
00:39:20,360 --> 00:39:21,990
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, I'll economize.</font>

630
00:39:22,237 --> 00:39:24,737
<font color="#FFFFFF">Only four cigars a day.</font>

631
00:39:24,823 --> 00:39:26,703
<font color="#FFFFFF">You are insufferable!</font>

632
00:39:30,913 --> 00:39:32,253
<font color="#FFFFFF">Is there anything else?</font>

633
00:39:32,956 --> 00:39:34,246
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes.</font>

634
00:39:34,333 --> 00:39:35,463
<font color="#FFFFFF">My love for you.</font>

635
00:39:36,418 --> 00:39:38,088
<font color="#FFFFFF">How much have you had
to drink this morning?</font>

636
00:39:40,088 --> 00:39:41,878
<font color="#FFFFFF">I see you now</font>

637
00:39:42,799 --> 00:39:44,879
<font color="#FFFFFF">as I first saw you</font>

638
00:39:45,093 --> 00:39:47,763
<font color="#FFFFFF">in 1904.</font>

639
00:39:47,846 --> 00:39:50,266
<font color="#FFFFFF">And I simply stood, speechless.</font>

640
00:39:50,349 --> 00:39:51,809
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, I must have been very beautiful</font>

641
00:39:51,892 --> 00:39:53,272
<font color="#FFFFFF">to achieve that miraculous effect.</font>

642
00:39:53,352 --> 00:39:56,022
<font color="#FFFFFF">Four years until we saw each other again.</font>

643
00:39:56,104 --> 00:39:57,314
<font color="#FFFFFF">Went by in an absolute flash.</font>

644
00:39:57,397 --> 00:39:59,267
<font color="#FFFFFF">You didn't lack for admirers.</font>

645
00:39:59,358 --> 00:40:03,488
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your fidele serviteur in Sidney peel.</font>

646
00:40:03,570 --> 00:40:05,360
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Brilliant man.
- Lionel earle.</font>

647
00:40:05,447 --> 00:40:07,407
<font color="#FFFFFF">Wonderful dancer.</font>

648
00:40:08,575 --> 00:40:11,195
<font color="#FFFFFF">And then at
lady St. Helier's dinner party.</font>

649
00:40:11,662 --> 00:40:13,412
<font color="#FFFFFF">Who should show up?</font>

650
00:40:14,581 --> 00:40:15,711
<font color="#FFFFFF">Pig.</font>

651
00:40:18,252 --> 00:40:19,502
<font color="#FFFFFF">Just the same.</font>

652
00:40:30,639 --> 00:40:32,059
<font color="#FFFFFF">Are we terribly old?</font>

653
00:40:33,183 --> 00:40:34,353
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes, I'm afraid you are.</font>

654
00:40:35,018 --> 00:40:36,558
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, you beast.</font>

655
00:40:36,645 --> 00:40:38,735
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, you...</font>

656
00:40:41,441 --> 00:40:44,111
<font color="#FFFFFF">Would you hear me read my speech</font>

657
00:40:44,194 --> 00:40:45,824
<font color="#FFFFFF">for tonight's broadcast?</font>

658
00:40:46,947 --> 00:40:48,157
<font color="#FFFFFF">Prime minister.</font>

659
00:40:48,240 --> 00:40:49,660
<font color="#FFFFFF">Prime minister, the situation in France.</font>

660
00:40:49,741 --> 00:40:51,951
<font color="#FFFFFF">Is it true we're in full retreat?</font>

661
00:40:52,035 --> 00:40:53,655
<font color="#FFFFFF">Is France lost?</font>

662
00:41:00,878 --> 00:41:03,548
<font color="#FFFFFF">"The Spanish ships I cannot see,</font>

663
00:41:03,630 --> 00:41:05,300
<font color="#FFFFFF">"for they are out of sight."</font>

664
00:41:06,091 --> 00:41:07,971
<font color="#FFFFFF">If you will sit here</font>

665
00:41:08,802 --> 00:41:10,432
<font color="#FFFFFF">at your desk.</font>

666
00:41:12,264 --> 00:41:14,684
<font color="#FFFFFF">And speak slowly and clearly.</font>

667
00:41:15,851 --> 00:41:17,061
<font color="#FFFFFF">Into the microphone.</font>

668
00:41:17,895 --> 00:41:18,905
<font color="#FFFFFF">So...</font>

669
00:41:19,396 --> 00:41:22,646
<font color="#FFFFFF">If you're ready, on the stroke of 9:00,</font>

670
00:41:22,733 --> 00:41:24,483
<font color="#FFFFFF">the red light will come on,</font>

671
00:41:24,568 --> 00:41:26,648
<font color="#FFFFFF">and we shall go live to the nation.</font>

672
00:41:28,906 --> 00:41:31,156
<font color="#FFFFFF">9:00, red light...</font>

673
00:41:32,492 --> 00:41:33,992
<font color="#FFFFFF">You begin.</font>

674
00:41:34,077 --> 00:41:35,407
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes?</font>

675
00:41:36,371 --> 00:41:37,371
<font color="#FFFFFF">One moment.</font>

676
00:41:44,796 --> 00:41:47,376
<font color="#FFFFFF">Prime minister, are we ready?</font>

677
00:41:47,466 --> 00:41:51,046
<font color="#FFFFFF">One moment, one moment.</font>

678
00:41:56,725 --> 00:41:58,765
<font color="#FFFFFF">We are going live...</font>

679
00:41:58,852 --> 00:42:00,402
<font color="#FFFFFF">One moment, damn you!</font>

680
00:42:07,236 --> 00:42:10,606
<font color="#FFFFFF">And four, three,</font>

681
00:42:11,031 --> 00:42:12,951
<font color="#FFFFFF">two, one.</font>

682
00:42:33,720 --> 00:42:36,770
<font color="#FFFFFF">I speak to you for the first time</font>

683
00:42:36,849 --> 00:42:38,679
<font color="#FFFFFF">as prime minister</font>

684
00:42:39,351 --> 00:42:43,811
<font color="#FFFFFF">in a solemn hour
for the life of our country,</font>

685
00:42:44,690 --> 00:42:48,230
<font color="#FFFFFF">of our empire, of our allies</font>

686
00:42:48,861 --> 00:42:52,611
<font color="#FFFFFF">and, above all, of the cause of freedom.</font>

687
00:42:53,949 --> 00:42:55,699
<font color="#FFFFFF">A tremendous battle</font>

688
00:42:55,784 --> 00:42:59,454
<font color="#FFFFFF">is raging in France and flanders.</font>

689
00:43:01,039 --> 00:43:04,829
<font color="#FFFFFF">The Germans, by a remarkable combination</font>

690
00:43:05,419 --> 00:43:09,299
<font color="#FFFFFF">of air bombing and heavily armored tanks,</font>

691
00:43:10,007 --> 00:43:12,757
<font color="#FFFFFF">have broken through the French defenses</font>

692
00:43:12,843 --> 00:43:15,723
<font color="#FFFFFF">north of the maginot line</font>

693
00:43:16,013 --> 00:43:17,473
<font color="#FFFFFF">and strong columns</font>

694
00:43:17,556 --> 00:43:18,926
<font color="#FFFFFF">of their armored vehicles</font>

695
00:43:19,016 --> 00:43:21,886
<font color="#FFFFFF">are ravaging the open country...</font>

696
00:43:23,187 --> 00:43:25,107
<font color="#FFFFFF">which, for the first day or two,</font>

697
00:43:25,230 --> 00:43:27,270
<font color="#FFFFFF">was without defenders.</font>

698
00:43:28,317 --> 00:43:33,697
<font color="#FFFFFF">However, I have invincible confidence</font>

699
00:43:34,114 --> 00:43:37,744
<font color="#FFFFFF">in the French army and its leaders.</font>

700
00:43:37,826 --> 00:43:40,946
<font color="#FFFFFF">Only a very small part
of that splendid army</font>

701
00:43:41,038 --> 00:43:43,418
<font color="#FFFFFF">has yet been heavily engaged,</font>

702
00:43:43,498 --> 00:43:48,958
<font color="#FFFFFF">and only a very small part
of France has yet been invaded.</font>

703
00:43:49,463 --> 00:43:50,923
<font color="#FFFFFF">Side by side,</font>

704
00:43:51,465 --> 00:43:55,265
<font color="#FFFFFF">the British and French peoples
have advanced.</font>

705
00:43:55,344 --> 00:43:58,474
<font color="#FFFFFF">- "Advanced"?
- To rescue not only Europe.</font>

706
00:43:58,555 --> 00:44:01,635
<font color="#FFFFFF">- How bloody dare he.
- But mankind</font>

707
00:44:01,725 --> 00:44:06,395
<font color="#FFFFFF">from the foulest and most
soul-destroying tyranny</font>

708
00:44:06,563 --> 00:44:09,023
<font color="#FFFFFF">which has ever darkened</font>

709
00:44:09,107 --> 00:44:11,937
<font color="#FFFFFF">and stained the pages of history.</font>

710
00:44:12,528 --> 00:44:16,198
<font color="#FFFFFF">But now one bond unites us all.</font>

711
00:44:16,782 --> 00:44:21,162
<font color="#FFFFFF">To wage war until victory is won,</font>

712
00:44:21,245 --> 00:44:24,295
<font color="#FFFFFF">and never to surrender ourselves</font>

713
00:44:24,915 --> 00:44:28,045
<font color="#FFFFFF">to servitude and shame.</font>

714
00:44:28,126 --> 00:44:29,706
<font color="#FFFFFF">Whatever the cost</font>

715
00:44:31,296 --> 00:44:32,956
<font color="#FFFFFF">and the agony may be,</font>

716
00:44:33,674 --> 00:44:36,134
<font color="#FFFFFF">conquer we must,</font>

717
00:44:36,802 --> 00:44:39,602
<font color="#FFFFFF">as conquer we shall.</font>

718
00:44:46,353 --> 00:44:47,603
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well done, sir.</font>

719
00:45:54,213 --> 00:45:57,303
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh! I thought you did marvelously.</font>

720
00:45:58,050 --> 00:45:59,470
<font color="#FFFFFF">The last ten years,</font>

721
00:45:59,551 --> 00:46:01,891
<font color="#FFFFFF">I was the only one
who told them the truth.</font>

722
00:46:02,471 --> 00:46:03,971
<font color="#FFFFFF">Until tonight.</font>

723
00:46:05,682 --> 00:46:07,272
<font color="#FFFFFF">There is no advance.</font>

724
00:46:09,603 --> 00:46:11,233
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's a shambles.</font>

725
00:46:12,272 --> 00:46:14,362
<font color="#FFFFFF">We're in full retreat.</font>

726
00:46:16,527 --> 00:46:18,027
<font color="#FFFFFF">But would you be serving them tonight</font>

727
00:46:18,111 --> 00:46:19,701
<font color="#FFFFFF">by denying them their sleep</font>

728
00:46:19,780 --> 00:46:21,660
<font color="#FFFFFF">and terrifying their children?</font>

729
00:46:22,157 --> 00:46:24,027
<font color="#FFFFFF">What, even if the terror is coming?</font>

730
00:46:24,117 --> 00:46:25,907
<font color="#FFFFFF">Because the terror is coming.</font>

731
00:46:27,621 --> 00:46:29,581
<font color="#FFFFFF">There's time enough for the truth.</font>

732
00:46:39,591 --> 00:46:41,221
<font color="#FFFFFF">Have you seen this?</font>

733
00:46:45,222 --> 00:46:47,182
<font color="#FFFFFF">What's so funny?</font>

734
00:46:48,559 --> 00:46:50,639
<font color="#FFFFFF">Prime minister. Sir.</font>

735
00:46:50,727 --> 00:46:51,977
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes, what is it?</font>

736
00:46:53,522 --> 00:46:54,812
<font color="#FFFFFF">Perhaps...</font>

737
00:46:58,360 --> 00:46:59,690
<font color="#FFFFFF">Look, I'm...</font>

738
00:46:59,778 --> 00:47:02,028
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm not sure if you know this, but,</font>

739
00:47:03,156 --> 00:47:05,076
<font color="#FFFFFF">but the way you're doing
your "v for victory" sign...</font>

740
00:47:06,994 --> 00:47:09,164
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, in the poorer quarters,</font>

741
00:47:09,454 --> 00:47:10,964
<font color="#FFFFFF">that gesture means something else.</font>

742
00:47:11,039 --> 00:47:12,499
<font color="#FFFFFF">What does it mean?</font>

743
00:47:12,583 --> 00:47:14,043
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, I wouldn't like to say, sir.</font>

744
00:47:14,126 --> 00:47:16,416
<font color="#FFFFFF">I was captured by the boer.</font>

745
00:47:16,503 --> 00:47:18,963
<font color="#FFFFFF">I spent time in a south African prison.</font>

746
00:47:19,590 --> 00:47:20,630
<font color="#FFFFFF">Up your bum.</font>

747
00:47:22,009 --> 00:47:23,049
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sir.</font>

748
00:47:23,760 --> 00:47:25,430
<font color="#FFFFFF">Up your bum?</font>

749
00:47:26,096 --> 00:47:27,136
<font color="#FFFFFF">Up your...</font>

750
00:47:30,058 --> 00:47:32,688
<font color="#FFFFFF">The way you're doing it, sir, yes, sir.</font>

751
00:47:34,062 --> 00:47:36,362
<font color="#FFFFFF">But if you turn it around, that's fine.</font>

752
00:47:38,275 --> 00:47:39,905
<font color="#FFFFFF">I wouldn't like millions of people</font>

753
00:47:39,985 --> 00:47:41,155
<font color="#FFFFFF">to take it the wrong way.</font>

754
00:47:41,236 --> 00:47:42,606
<font color="#FFFFFF">Indeed.</font>

755
00:47:43,238 --> 00:47:44,698
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Sir.
- Sir.</font>

756
00:47:45,616 --> 00:47:48,906
<font color="#FFFFFF">And up your bum!</font>

757
00:47:49,036 --> 00:47:50,116
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your majesty.</font>

758
00:47:50,621 --> 00:47:52,831
<font color="#FFFFFF">Don't want to take
too much of your time.</font>

759
00:47:53,457 --> 00:47:55,377
<font color="#FFFFFF">I heard you on the wireless.</font>

760
00:47:56,543 --> 00:47:58,253
<font color="#FFFFFF">Was I comprehensible?</font>

761
00:47:59,296 --> 00:48:03,216
<font color="#FFFFFF">The public need to be led, not misled.</font>

762
00:48:03,300 --> 00:48:06,010
<font color="#FFFFFF">Not left to work it out for themselves.</font>

763
00:48:09,806 --> 00:48:11,016
<font color="#FFFFFF">Right.</font>

764
00:48:11,391 --> 00:48:13,391
<font color="#FFFFFF">Will that be all, your majesty?</font>

765
00:48:13,644 --> 00:48:14,644
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes.</font>

766
00:48:14,728 --> 00:48:16,148
<font color="#FFFFFF">Good day, prime minister.</font>

767
00:48:16,230 --> 00:48:17,440
<font color="#FFFFFF">Good day.</font>

768
00:48:20,943 --> 00:48:25,163
<font color="#FFFFFF">I believe I have just received
a royal rap on the knuckles.</font>

769
00:48:31,662 --> 00:48:33,372
<font color="#FFFFFF">As of 20:00 hours last night,</font>

770
00:48:33,455 --> 00:48:36,825
<font color="#FFFFFF">the Germans have encircled 60 British,</font>

771
00:48:36,917 --> 00:48:38,997
<font color="#FFFFFF">Belgian and French divisions.</font>

772
00:48:40,212 --> 00:48:43,972
<font color="#FFFFFF">On our part, all our forces
under lord gort have withdrawn</font>

773
00:48:44,049 --> 00:48:47,009
<font color="#FFFFFF">or are trying to withdraw
to the French coast, to dunkirk,</font>

774
00:48:47,344 --> 00:48:49,144
<font color="#FFFFFF">where we cannot reach them.</font>

775
00:48:49,221 --> 00:48:50,851
<font color="#FFFFFF">How many of our men are trapped?</font>

776
00:48:50,931 --> 00:48:52,311
<font color="#FFFFFF">All of them.</font>

777
00:48:52,766 --> 00:48:55,266
<font color="#FFFFFF">Our country's entire
professional soldiery.</font>

778
00:48:55,686 --> 00:48:58,056
<font color="#FFFFFF">And we can see no clear way
to rescue them.</font>

779
00:49:01,608 --> 00:49:04,238
<font color="#FFFFFF">General, are you telling me</font>

780
00:49:04,319 --> 00:49:08,369
<font color="#FFFFFF">that we shall have lost
the entire British army</font>

781
00:49:08,448 --> 00:49:09,988
<font color="#FFFFFF">by the next few days?</font>

782
00:49:10,993 --> 00:49:12,083
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's correct.</font>

783
00:49:12,828 --> 00:49:16,158
<font color="#FFFFFF">The German force
is superior in every regard</font>

784
00:49:16,248 --> 00:49:18,208
<font color="#FFFFFF">and only 50 miles from the coast.</font>

785
00:49:18,292 --> 00:49:20,502
<font color="#FFFFFF">They are pushing us into the sea.</font>

786
00:49:20,586 --> 00:49:23,956
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, the Germans must not reach the sea.</font>

787
00:49:24,423 --> 00:49:27,843
<font color="#FFFFFF">Not before we evacuate our men.</font>

788
00:49:27,926 --> 00:49:29,836
<font color="#FFFFFF">Ismay, what have you got for us?</font>

789
00:49:29,928 --> 00:49:31,258
<font color="#FFFFFF">As it stands, I cannot see</font>

790
00:49:31,346 --> 00:49:35,056
<font color="#FFFFFF">we have much hope of getting
any of our forces out in time.</font>

791
00:49:36,727 --> 00:49:38,307
<font color="#FFFFFF">Not a man?</font>

792
00:49:39,771 --> 00:49:42,441
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, we... well, we cannot be so</font>

793
00:49:42,691 --> 00:49:44,191
<font color="#FFFFFF">totally at their mercy.</font>

794
00:49:44,276 --> 00:49:45,816
<font color="#FFFFFF">What's our next step?</font>

795
00:49:46,695 --> 00:49:47,985
<font color="#FFFFFF">Anyone?</font>

796
00:49:49,072 --> 00:49:50,162
<font color="#FFFFFF">Come on, speak!</font>

797
00:49:53,327 --> 00:49:54,657
<font color="#FFFFFF">We still have a Garrison at calais.</font>

798
00:49:54,745 --> 00:49:56,005
<font color="#FFFFFF">25 miles to the west.</font>

799
00:49:56,079 --> 00:49:57,659
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, how many men do we have there?</font>

800
00:49:57,748 --> 00:49:59,078
<font color="#FFFFFF">4,000, more or less.</font>

801
00:50:01,793 --> 00:50:04,213
<font color="#FFFFFF">Then why... why didn't you say so?</font>

802
00:50:05,255 --> 00:50:08,585
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes. Then we... we have them go east,</font>

803
00:50:08,675 --> 00:50:11,045
<font color="#FFFFFF">engage with the German columns
moving on dunkirk,</font>

804
00:50:11,136 --> 00:50:12,296
<font color="#FFFFFF">buy us some time.</font>

805
00:50:12,387 --> 00:50:14,967
<font color="#FFFFFF">Draw the... the Nazi focus</font>

806
00:50:15,057 --> 00:50:17,887
<font color="#FFFFFF">away from dunkirk whilst we execute a...</font>

807
00:50:17,976 --> 00:50:20,346
<font color="#FFFFFF">A maritime evacuation of our forces.</font>

808
00:50:20,437 --> 00:50:21,897
<font color="#FFFFFF">Is that possible?</font>

809
00:50:21,980 --> 00:50:23,360
<font color="#FFFFFF">It would mean a huge sacrifice.</font>

810
00:50:23,440 --> 00:50:25,360
<font color="#FFFFFF">4,000 young men.</font>

811
00:50:25,442 --> 00:50:28,402
<font color="#FFFFFF">To save 300,000.</font>

812
00:50:28,487 --> 00:50:31,107
<font color="#FFFFFF">Under whose command
is the calais Garrison?</font>

813
00:50:31,198 --> 00:50:32,568
<font color="#FFFFFF">Brigadier Nicholson.</font>

814
00:50:32,658 --> 00:50:33,908
<font color="#FFFFFF">Very well.</font>

815
00:50:35,536 --> 00:50:37,406
<font color="#FFFFFF">Tell Nicholson it is
of the greatest importance</font>

816
00:50:37,496 --> 00:50:39,206
<font color="#FFFFFF">to this island that...</font>

817
00:50:39,289 --> 00:50:42,379
<font color="#FFFFFF">That his Garrison draw the enemy's tanks</font>

818
00:50:42,459 --> 00:50:44,669
<font color="#FFFFFF">and artillery and bombers
away from dunkirk.</font>

819
00:50:44,753 --> 00:50:46,923
<font color="#FFFFFF">Invite their wrath, and...</font>

820
00:50:48,674 --> 00:50:50,184
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, and to fight on</font>

821
00:50:51,510 --> 00:50:52,970
<font color="#FFFFFF">if needs be.</font>

822
00:50:56,682 --> 00:51:00,392
<font color="#FFFFFF">If needs be,
until the destruction of his command.</font>

823
00:51:03,105 --> 00:51:04,775
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's suicide.</font>

824
00:51:16,577 --> 00:51:20,287
<font color="#FFFFFF">Prime minister, I have reservations.</font>

825
00:51:20,914 --> 00:51:23,464
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, who is free of reservations?</font>

826
00:51:23,917 --> 00:51:25,747
<font color="#FFFFFF">About unnecessary sacrifice,</font>

827
00:51:26,211 --> 00:51:27,801
<font color="#FFFFFF">when there is an available alternative.</font>

828
00:51:29,423 --> 00:51:30,763
<font color="#FFFFFF">What alternative?</font>

829
00:51:31,550 --> 00:51:33,640
<font color="#FFFFFF">Italy has offered to mediate peace talks</font>

830
00:51:34,178 --> 00:51:35,598
<font color="#FFFFFF">between ourselves and Germany.</font>

831
00:51:35,679 --> 00:51:36,929
<font color="#FFFFFF">I already indicated that,</font>

832
00:51:37,014 --> 00:51:38,314
<font color="#FFFFFF">provided the Liberty and independence</font>

833
00:51:38,390 --> 00:51:39,970
<font color="#FFFFFF">of the British empire was assured,</font>

834
00:51:40,559 --> 00:51:42,479
<font color="#FFFFFF">we would consider any proposal.</font>

835
00:51:42,561 --> 00:51:47,321
<font color="#FFFFFF">With, with Hitler holding the whip hand.</font>

836
00:51:47,399 --> 00:51:49,029
<font color="#FFFFFF">Do you really think he would honor</font>

837
00:51:49,109 --> 00:51:50,319
<font color="#FFFFFF">our Liberty and independence?</font>

838
00:51:50,694 --> 00:51:52,744
<font color="#FFFFFF">It would be in his interest to do so, sir.</font>

839
00:51:53,113 --> 00:51:55,243
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Because the British empire...
- The only thing to do</font>

840
00:51:55,324 --> 00:51:58,244
<font color="#FFFFFF">is to show that maniac</font>

841
00:51:58,327 --> 00:52:00,367
<font color="#FFFFFF">that he cannot conquer this island,</font>

842
00:52:00,454 --> 00:52:02,084
<font color="#FFFFFF">and for that we need an army.</font>

843
00:52:02,164 --> 00:52:03,424
<font color="#FFFFFF">General, tell brigadier Nicholson</font>

844
00:52:03,498 --> 00:52:04,958
<font color="#FFFFFF">the Germans must not reach the sea.</font>

845
00:52:05,042 --> 00:52:07,922
<font color="#FFFFFF">Not before we-we get our boys</font>

846
00:52:08,003 --> 00:52:10,053
<font color="#FFFFFF">off of that bloody beach!</font>

847
00:52:10,130 --> 00:52:11,920
<font color="#FFFFFF">I take full responsibility.</font>

848
00:52:12,007 --> 00:52:13,257
<font color="#FFFFFF">Really?</font>

849
00:52:13,342 --> 00:52:15,262
<font color="#FFFFFF">Really! Yes, sir.</font>

850
00:52:15,344 --> 00:52:16,724
<font color="#FFFFFF">It is the reason</font>

851
00:52:16,803 --> 00:52:19,223
<font color="#FFFFFF">I sit in this chair!</font>

852
00:52:22,434 --> 00:52:23,984
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, surely, before you take</font>

853
00:52:24,061 --> 00:52:26,731
<font color="#FFFFFF">full responsibility
for the deaths of 4,000 men,</font>

854
00:52:26,813 --> 00:52:30,113
<font color="#FFFFFF">you'd wish to consider
every available Avenue.</font>

855
00:52:32,569 --> 00:52:34,859
<font color="#FFFFFF">What is this?</font>

856
00:52:36,323 --> 00:52:39,203
<font color="#FFFFFF">What is your mind
on the principle of peace talks, sir?</font>

857
00:52:43,038 --> 00:52:46,168
<font color="#FFFFFF">Do we take it, for example,
that you preclude yourself</font>

858
00:52:46,250 --> 00:52:49,790
<font color="#FFFFFF">from even considering
taking part in such negotiations?</font>

859
00:53:09,690 --> 00:53:13,440
<font color="#FFFFFF">I should like to speak to viscount halifax</font>

860
00:53:13,527 --> 00:53:15,357
<font color="#FFFFFF">and Mr. Chamberlain.</font>

861
00:53:16,071 --> 00:53:17,321
<font color="#FFFFFF">Alone.</font>

862
00:53:18,156 --> 00:53:20,986
<font color="#FFFFFF">Issue the order to the calais Garrison.</font>

863
00:53:21,910 --> 00:53:23,580
<font color="#FFFFFF">Confirm it has been done.</font>

864
00:53:24,037 --> 00:53:25,327
<font color="#FFFFFF">Dismissed.</font>

865
00:53:27,207 --> 00:53:28,747
<font color="#FFFFFF">Now, you two come on.</font>

866
00:53:28,834 --> 00:53:30,044
<font color="#FFFFFF">Out.</font>

867
00:53:32,129 --> 00:53:33,169
<font color="#FFFFFF">Bridges!</font>

868
00:53:33,255 --> 00:53:34,885
<font color="#FFFFFF">You come on, hop it!</font>

869
00:53:34,965 --> 00:53:36,475
<font color="#FFFFFF">Out. Out!</font>

870
00:54:45,369 --> 00:54:46,659
<font color="#FFFFFF">Winston,</font>

871
00:54:47,913 --> 00:54:50,333
<font color="#FFFFFF">we are facing certain defeat on land,</font>

872
00:54:50,999 --> 00:54:55,049
<font color="#FFFFFF">the annihilation of our army,
and imminent invasion.</font>

873
00:54:55,879 --> 00:54:57,629
<font color="#FFFFFF">We must be rational.</font>

874
00:54:57,714 --> 00:55:00,554
<font color="#FFFFFF">We are a seagoing nation.</font>

875
00:55:00,634 --> 00:55:03,854
<font color="#FFFFFF">Have been since the bronze age.</font>

876
00:55:04,680 --> 00:55:06,430
<font color="#FFFFFF">The channel is ours.</font>

877
00:55:06,515 --> 00:55:09,395
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's our moat, our battlement,</font>

878
00:55:09,476 --> 00:55:12,096
<font color="#FFFFFF">and the German doesn't
recognize an expanse of water</font>

879
00:55:12,187 --> 00:55:14,107
<font color="#FFFFFF">greater than a bloody lake.</font>

880
00:55:14,231 --> 00:55:17,781
<font color="#FFFFFF">They have first to reach
this island, Edward.</font>

881
00:55:17,860 --> 00:55:19,530
<font color="#FFFFFF">Where men, women and children,</font>

882
00:55:19,611 --> 00:55:21,611
<font color="#FFFFFF">whom we will have failed despicably</font>

883
00:55:21,697 --> 00:55:23,657
<font color="#FFFFFF">in our duty of protection, will be</font>

884
00:55:23,740 --> 00:55:25,700
<font color="#FFFFFF">- entirely defenseless...
- And whose fault is that?</font>

885
00:55:25,784 --> 00:55:28,754
<font color="#FFFFFF">against the largest army
the world has ever seen.</font>

886
00:55:28,829 --> 00:55:30,459
<font color="#FFFFFF">Furthermore, once France falls,</font>

887
00:55:30,539 --> 00:55:33,329
<font color="#FFFFFF">Germany can concentrate
on aircraft production.</font>

888
00:55:33,417 --> 00:55:35,787
<font color="#FFFFFF">They will then have
the French fleet as well.</font>

889
00:55:35,878 --> 00:55:38,338
<font color="#FFFFFF">What is to stop
herr Hitler then, Winston?</font>

890
00:55:38,422 --> 00:55:41,802
<font color="#FFFFFF">Words, words, words alone.</font>

891
00:55:43,760 --> 00:55:45,930
<font color="#FFFFFF">If you will not permit any talk of peace,</font>

892
00:55:46,013 --> 00:55:47,223
<font color="#FFFFFF">then I shall be forced...</font>

893
00:55:47,306 --> 00:55:49,096
<font color="#FFFFFF">Might we not allow Edward</font>

894
00:55:49,183 --> 00:55:52,943
<font color="#FFFFFF">simply to meet the
Italian ambassador bastianini,</font>

895
00:55:53,020 --> 00:55:55,270
<font color="#FFFFFF">discuss a possible role</font>

896
00:55:55,355 --> 00:55:58,685
<font color="#FFFFFF">as mediators between us and Germany,</font>

897
00:56:00,068 --> 00:56:01,358
<font color="#FFFFFF">and find out their price?</font>

898
00:56:18,212 --> 00:56:19,302
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sir.</font>

899
00:56:39,650 --> 00:56:42,190
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Mr. President.
- Winston.</font>

900
00:56:42,277 --> 00:56:43,947
<font color="#FFFFFF">Franklin.</font>

901
00:56:44,154 --> 00:56:47,374
<font color="#FFFFFF">- How are you?
- Fine. Fine.</font>

902
00:56:47,449 --> 00:56:49,119
<font color="#FFFFFF">How are you, prime minister?</font>

903
00:56:49,451 --> 00:56:51,241
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, I'm in fine fettle.</font>

904
00:56:51,370 --> 00:56:52,500
<font color="#FFFFFF">Fine fettle.</font>

905
00:56:52,579 --> 00:56:54,459
<font color="#FFFFFF">Listen.</font>

906
00:56:54,748 --> 00:56:59,628
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm, telephoning about your Navy ships.</font>

907
00:56:59,711 --> 00:57:02,171
<font color="#FFFFFF">If you could loan us just,</font>

908
00:57:02,923 --> 00:57:05,593
<font color="#FFFFFF">50 older destroyers.</font>

909
00:57:05,676 --> 00:57:08,846
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Ah, yes.
- Or even 40 would do.</font>

910
00:57:09,471 --> 00:57:11,141
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, I,</font>

911
00:57:11,223 --> 00:57:13,063
<font color="#FFFFFF">I did ask around,</font>

912
00:57:13,559 --> 00:57:16,689
<font color="#FFFFFF">but just not possible, I'm afraid.</font>

913
00:57:16,979 --> 00:57:21,649
<font color="#FFFFFF">The neutrality act we signed
last year has tied my hands.</font>

914
00:57:21,733 --> 00:57:23,323
<font color="#FFFFFF">Just can't swing it.</font>

915
00:57:23,694 --> 00:57:24,784
<font color="#FFFFFF">I tried.</font>

916
00:57:24,862 --> 00:57:26,572
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, can I...</font>

917
00:57:28,532 --> 00:57:32,412
<font color="#FFFFFF">Do I have your permission</font>

918
00:57:32,494 --> 00:57:35,164
<font color="#FFFFFF">to send an aircraft carrier</font>

919
00:57:35,247 --> 00:57:37,167
<font color="#FFFFFF">to pick up the p-40 fighter planes</font>

920
00:57:37,249 --> 00:57:38,669
<font color="#FFFFFF">we purchased from you?</font>

921
00:57:42,588 --> 00:57:44,168
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mr. President?</font>

922
00:57:44,965 --> 00:57:47,135
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, you've got me there again.</font>

923
00:57:47,217 --> 00:57:49,757
<font color="#FFFFFF">New law preventing transshipment</font>

924
00:57:49,845 --> 00:57:51,685
<font color="#FFFFFF">of military equipment.</font>

925
00:57:51,763 --> 00:57:53,933
<font color="#FFFFFF">But we paid for them.</font>

926
00:57:54,224 --> 00:57:56,814
<font color="#FFFFFF">We paid for them with the money that we...</font>

927
00:57:56,894 --> 00:57:58,604
<font color="#FFFFFF">That we borrowed from you.</font>

928
00:57:58,812 --> 00:58:01,942
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm so, so sorry, Winston.</font>

929
00:58:06,361 --> 00:58:09,701
<font color="#FFFFFF">I need not impress upon you the...</font>

930
00:58:10,365 --> 00:58:14,615
<font color="#FFFFFF">The trouble faced
by the western hemisphere,</font>

931
00:58:15,787 --> 00:58:19,917
<font color="#FFFFFF">without your support in some fashion.</font>

932
00:58:20,000 --> 00:58:21,840
<font color="#FFFFFF">I know. I know.</font>

933
00:58:21,919 --> 00:58:24,709
<font color="#FFFFFF">You are on my mind day and night.</font>

934
00:58:27,007 --> 00:58:30,587
<font color="#FFFFFF">Look, we could possibly...</font>

935
00:58:30,677 --> 00:58:32,637
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mr. President...</font>

936
00:58:32,721 --> 00:58:34,391
<font color="#FFFFFF">I mean to say...</font>

937
00:58:34,473 --> 00:58:39,893
<font color="#FFFFFF">We are facing the gravest odds.</font>

938
00:58:39,978 --> 00:58:41,398
<font color="#FFFFFF">We could take your planes</font>

939
00:58:41,480 --> 00:58:44,020
<font color="#FFFFFF">to about a mile from the Canadian border.</font>

940
00:58:44,900 --> 00:58:46,740
<font color="#FFFFFF">And then, if you send across</font>

941
00:58:46,818 --> 00:58:51,408
<font color="#FFFFFF">a team of horses from Canada,
nothing motorized</font>

942
00:58:51,490 --> 00:58:54,330
<font color="#FFFFFF">then you could pull them
over the border yourself.</font>

943
00:58:56,203 --> 00:58:58,203
<font color="#FFFFFF">How does that sound?</font>

944
00:59:01,416 --> 00:59:02,746
<font color="#FFFFFF">Horses?</font>

945
00:59:04,294 --> 00:59:06,714
<font color="#FFFFFF">You did say,</font>

946
00:59:06,797 --> 00:59:09,297
<font color="#FFFFFF">a team of horses?</font>

947
00:59:09,800 --> 00:59:12,760
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, I guess you could
push them yourself.</font>

948
00:59:13,387 --> 00:59:15,387
<font color="#FFFFFF">Damn things have wheels.</font>

949
00:59:18,350 --> 00:59:19,480
<font color="#FFFFFF">Up to you.</font>

950
00:59:23,146 --> 00:59:25,816
<font color="#FFFFFF">We could do that, prime minister.</font>

951
00:59:29,486 --> 00:59:30,696
<font color="#FFFFFF">Prime minister?</font>

952
00:59:34,700 --> 00:59:37,580
<font color="#FFFFFF">Anything you could do at this time,</font>

953
00:59:37,661 --> 00:59:39,661
<font color="#FFFFFF">Franklin, would be most welcome.</font>

954
00:59:40,789 --> 00:59:42,829
<font color="#FFFFFF">Good night to you, Winston.</font>

955
00:59:43,208 --> 00:59:45,338
<font color="#FFFFFF">It must be late there.</font>

956
00:59:46,295 --> 00:59:51,225
<font color="#FFFFFF">In more ways than you could possibly know.</font>

957
01:00:25,542 --> 01:00:28,342
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Prime minister.
- Prime minister.</font>

958
01:00:36,720 --> 01:00:39,470
<font color="#FFFFFF">Get me admiral ramsay
on one of these, will you?</font>

959
01:00:39,556 --> 01:00:41,806
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes, prime minister.</font>

960
01:00:42,309 --> 01:00:44,519
<font color="#FFFFFF">Put me through to admiral ramsay.</font>

961
01:01:03,497 --> 01:01:05,077
<font color="#FFFFFF">Admiral ramsay.</font>

962
01:01:05,165 --> 01:01:06,995
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's the prime minister.</font>

963
01:01:08,126 --> 01:01:09,376
<font color="#FFFFFF">Bertie?</font>

964
01:01:09,920 --> 01:01:13,300
<font color="#FFFFFF">Bertie, I hope I didn't wake you.</font>

965
01:01:13,382 --> 01:01:16,132
<font color="#FFFFFF">Not at all. I was just reading the Bible.</font>

966
01:01:16,218 --> 01:01:18,178
<font color="#FFFFFF">Exodus?</font>

967
01:01:19,096 --> 01:01:20,676
<font color="#FFFFFF">Listen, bertie.</font>

968
01:01:21,139 --> 01:01:23,479
<font color="#FFFFFF">We need to evacuate our boys.</font>

969
01:01:23,559 --> 01:01:26,729
<font color="#FFFFFF">The Navy is saying that with one cruiser</font>

970
01:01:26,812 --> 01:01:28,652
<font color="#FFFFFF">and six destroyers and with the...</font>

971
01:01:28,730 --> 01:01:31,730
<font color="#FFFFFF">The luftwaffe controlling the skies above,</font>

972
01:01:31,817 --> 01:01:33,777
<font color="#FFFFFF">we'll be lucky to get ten percent out.</font>

973
01:01:34,111 --> 01:01:38,781
<font color="#FFFFFF">I want you to order an assembly of boats.</font>

974
01:01:40,492 --> 01:01:41,952
<font color="#FFFFFF">Boats?</font>

975
01:01:42,035 --> 01:01:43,325
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes.</font>

976
01:01:43,412 --> 01:01:45,412
<font color="#FFFFFF">Civilian boats.</font>

977
01:01:45,497 --> 01:01:48,537
<font color="#FFFFFF">As many as you can get your hands on.</font>

978
01:01:48,625 --> 01:01:51,625
<font color="#FFFFFF">Longley's clipper,
fearnley's gin palace,</font>

979
01:01:51,712 --> 01:01:54,132
<font color="#FFFFFF">anyone with a pleasure craft
bigger than 30 foot</font>

980
01:01:54,214 --> 01:01:55,634
<font color="#FFFFFF">that can get to France.</font>

981
01:01:58,135 --> 01:01:59,935
<font color="#FFFFFF">Bertie, you still there?</font>

982
01:02:00,762 --> 01:02:02,182
<font color="#FFFFFF">Um... right.</font>

983
01:02:04,099 --> 01:02:07,309
<font color="#FFFFFF">Help me stage this thing, bertie?</font>

984
01:02:07,895 --> 01:02:11,945
<font color="#FFFFFF">We must at least try to bring
some of our boys home.</font>

985
01:02:13,192 --> 01:02:15,322
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, I'll have the BBC issue the order.</font>

986
01:02:15,736 --> 01:02:16,946
<font color="#FFFFFF">Good.</font>

987
01:02:17,029 --> 01:02:19,569
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, and bertie, you still there?</font>

988
01:02:20,699 --> 01:02:23,029
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Sir.
- We need a name</font>

989
01:02:23,827 --> 01:02:25,117
<font color="#FFFFFF">for this operation.</font>

990
01:02:28,248 --> 01:02:29,998
<font color="#FFFFFF">Good morning, prime minister.
Prime minister, do you have</font>

991
01:02:30,083 --> 01:02:31,423
<font color="#FFFFFF">anything you'd like to say
to our readers this morning?</font>

992
01:02:31,502 --> 01:02:33,212
<font color="#FFFFFF">Prime minister. Mr. Churchill, sir.</font>

993
01:02:33,295 --> 01:02:34,845
<font color="#FFFFFF">Prime minister, do you have
anything you'd like to say?</font>

994
01:02:34,922 --> 01:02:37,012
<font color="#FFFFFF">Prime minister?
Prime minister, are you going to...</font>

995
01:02:37,090 --> 01:02:38,880
<font color="#FFFFFF">Prime minister, would you like to...
Prime minister?</font>

996
01:02:46,683 --> 01:02:49,143
<font color="#FFFFFF">How do you manage drinking during the day?</font>

997
01:02:53,440 --> 01:02:54,610
<font color="#FFFFFF">Practice.</font>

998
01:03:13,043 --> 01:03:14,043
<font color="#FFFFFF">I...</font>

999
01:03:15,087 --> 01:03:16,797
<font color="#FFFFFF">Should like to discuss...</font>

1000
01:03:17,005 --> 01:03:20,295
<font color="#FFFFFF">I have been asked if plans should be drawn</font>

1001
01:03:20,384 --> 01:03:24,974
<font color="#FFFFFF">to evacuate myself
and my family to Canada.</font>

1002
01:03:26,098 --> 01:03:28,728
<font color="#FFFFFF">I would like to know
the opinion of our prime minister.</font>

1003
01:03:30,602 --> 01:03:32,482
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, my opinion would be that you must do</font>

1004
01:03:32,563 --> 01:03:34,813
<font color="#FFFFFF">what you feel is right for yourself,</font>

1005
01:03:35,691 --> 01:03:38,691
<font color="#FFFFFF">your family and the nation.</font>

1006
01:03:40,028 --> 01:03:42,448
<font color="#FFFFFF">I mean, your survival is Paramount.</font>

1007
01:03:43,699 --> 01:03:45,529
<font color="#FFFFFF">Prime ministers...</font>

1008
01:03:45,617 --> 01:03:48,867
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, we seem to come and go
at an astonishing rate.</font>

1009
01:03:49,288 --> 01:03:52,328
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your position in parliament, I...</font>

1010
01:03:53,083 --> 01:03:55,423
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm told, is not strong.</font>

1011
01:03:56,920 --> 01:03:58,420
<font color="#FFFFFF">My party</font>

1012
01:03:59,464 --> 01:04:05,224
<font color="#FFFFFF">resents the way
Chamberlain was pushed aside.</font>

1013
01:04:05,304 --> 01:04:06,934
<font color="#FFFFFF">And many others doubt me.</font>

1014
01:04:07,347 --> 01:04:08,847
<font color="#FFFFFF">They want halifax still,</font>

1015
01:04:08,932 --> 01:04:11,062
<font color="#FFFFFF">but why get rid of the organ grinder</font>

1016
01:04:11,143 --> 01:04:12,643
<font color="#FFFFFF">and replace him with the monkey?</font>

1017
01:04:12,728 --> 01:04:15,938
<font color="#FFFFFF">Lord halifax is
a close personal friend of mine.</font>

1018
01:04:21,695 --> 01:04:23,565
<font color="#FFFFFF">I am unwanted.</font>

1019
01:04:26,158 --> 01:04:29,788
<font color="#FFFFFF">I've never been trusted
since the gallipoli campaign.</font>

1020
01:04:31,205 --> 01:04:32,545
<font color="#FFFFFF">Unwanted.</font>

1021
01:04:33,248 --> 01:04:35,418
<font color="#FFFFFF">Perhaps it's because you scare people.</font>

1022
01:04:35,876 --> 01:04:37,036
<font color="#FFFFFF">Who?</font>

1023
01:04:37,127 --> 01:04:38,207
<font color="#FFFFFF">You scare me.</font>

1024
01:04:39,338 --> 01:04:40,708
<font color="#FFFFFF">What nonsense.</font>

1025
01:04:42,841 --> 01:04:46,091
<font color="#FFFFFF">What could possibly be scary about me?</font>

1026
01:04:46,220 --> 01:04:49,220
<font color="#FFFFFF">One never knows what's going
to come out of your mouth next.</font>

1027
01:04:49,306 --> 01:04:51,016
<font color="#FFFFFF">Something that will flatter,</font>

1028
01:04:51,099 --> 01:04:52,979
<font color="#FFFFFF">something that will wound.</font>

1029
01:04:58,106 --> 01:05:01,736
<font color="#FFFFFF">My emotions are unbridled.</font>

1030
01:05:03,570 --> 01:05:05,990
<font color="#FFFFFF">A wildness in the blood</font>

1031
01:05:06,073 --> 01:05:09,533
<font color="#FFFFFF">I share with my father.</font>

1032
01:05:10,536 --> 01:05:12,696
<font color="#FFFFFF">And my mother also.</font>

1033
01:05:13,539 --> 01:05:16,459
<font color="#FFFFFF">We lacked the gift of temperance.</font>

1034
01:05:18,877 --> 01:05:20,337
<font color="#FFFFFF">Were you close to your parents?</font>

1035
01:05:20,629 --> 01:05:24,219
<font color="#FFFFFF">My mother was glamorous,</font>

1036
01:05:25,592 --> 01:05:28,092
<font color="#FFFFFF">but perhaps too widely loved.</font>

1037
01:05:29,555 --> 01:05:32,475
<font color="#FFFFFF">My father was like god,</font>

1038
01:05:33,058 --> 01:05:34,558
<font color="#FFFFFF">busy elsewhere.</font>

1039
01:05:35,853 --> 01:05:36,853
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hmm.</font>

1040
01:06:18,437 --> 01:06:19,937
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Good day, gentlemen.
- Prime minister.</font>

1041
01:06:20,022 --> 01:06:25,692
<font color="#FFFFFF">I have asked the minister for war
to join us.</font>

1042
01:06:25,944 --> 01:06:28,454
<font color="#FFFFFF">Neville, would you...</font>

1043
01:06:28,572 --> 01:06:29,862
<font color="#FFFFFF">Anthony.</font>

1044
01:06:32,034 --> 01:06:36,794
<font color="#FFFFFF">Obviously, we are
in a dangerous situation.</font>

1045
01:06:37,164 --> 01:06:39,544
<font color="#FFFFFF">But I am assured by the French premier</font>

1046
01:06:39,625 --> 01:06:42,635
<font color="#FFFFFF">that while some German tank units</font>

1047
01:06:42,711 --> 01:06:44,751
<font color="#FFFFFF">have reached the sea,</font>

1048
01:06:45,380 --> 01:06:47,880
<font color="#FFFFFF">the situation generally seems
to be well in hand.</font>

1049
01:06:47,966 --> 01:06:50,546
<font color="#FFFFFF">What news from calais?</font>

1050
01:06:50,636 --> 01:06:52,506
<font color="#FFFFFF">The Garrison attacked, but was forced back</font>

1051
01:06:52,596 --> 01:06:54,556
<font color="#FFFFFF">and is now surrounded on all sides.</font>

1052
01:06:55,557 --> 01:06:57,887
<font color="#FFFFFF">They're being shelled
and bombed mercilessly.</font>

1053
01:06:58,310 --> 01:06:59,980
<font color="#FFFFFF">Casualties are at 60%.</font>

1054
01:07:04,024 --> 01:07:05,034
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hmm.</font>

1055
01:07:11,240 --> 01:07:12,740
<font color="#FFFFFF">Prime minister.</font>

1056
01:07:13,492 --> 01:07:14,952
<font color="#FFFFFF">The question of peace talks.</font>

1057
01:07:15,994 --> 01:07:17,834
<font color="#FFFFFF">We must hold our nerve.</font>

1058
01:07:18,580 --> 01:07:23,000
<font color="#FFFFFF">Signal only that we intend
to fight it out until the end.</font>

1059
01:07:23,418 --> 01:07:25,248
<font color="#FFFFFF">A peace offer</font>

1060
01:07:25,379 --> 01:07:27,169
<font color="#FFFFFF">- telegraphs our weakness.
- Agreed.</font>

1061
01:07:27,256 --> 01:07:29,666
<font color="#FFFFFF">And even if we were beaten,
we should be no worse off</font>

1062
01:07:29,758 --> 01:07:32,218
<font color="#FFFFFF">than we should be if we were
now to abandon the struggle.</font>

1063
01:07:32,803 --> 01:07:34,513
<font color="#FFFFFF">Let us therefore avoid</font>

1064
01:07:34,596 --> 01:07:37,886
<font color="#FFFFFF">being dragged down the slippery slope</font>

1065
01:07:37,975 --> 01:07:40,105
<font color="#FFFFFF">with talk of a negotiated peace.</font>

1066
01:07:40,185 --> 01:07:42,265
<font color="#FFFFFF">Slippery slope? The only...</font>

1067
01:07:42,354 --> 01:07:45,574
<font color="#FFFFFF">- I suspect Italy and Germany...
- The only slippery slope...</font>

1068
01:07:45,649 --> 01:07:48,229
<font color="#FFFFFF">wish to get us so deeply
involved in negotiations</font>

1069
01:07:48,318 --> 01:07:51,198
<font color="#FFFFFF">- that we should be unable to turn back.
- Nonsense.</font>

1070
01:07:51,280 --> 01:07:53,320
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Bastianini informed me...
- I propose...</font>

1071
01:07:53,407 --> 01:07:55,777
<font color="#FFFFFF">- The only slippery slope...
- Would you stop interrupting me</font>

1072
01:07:55,868 --> 01:07:57,828
<font color="#FFFFFF">while I am interrupting you?</font>

1073
01:08:01,874 --> 01:08:04,254
<font color="#FFFFFF">When I chose my war cabinet,
I took great care</font>

1074
01:08:04,334 --> 01:08:06,964
<font color="#FFFFFF">to surround myself with old rivals.</font>

1075
01:08:08,172 --> 01:08:09,592
<font color="#FFFFFF">I may have overdone it.</font>

1076
01:08:10,465 --> 01:08:12,045
<font color="#FFFFFF">Viscount halifax,</font>

1077
01:08:12,384 --> 01:08:16,104
<font color="#FFFFFF">the approach you propose is...
It's not only...</font>

1078
01:08:16,180 --> 01:08:17,760
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's futile.</font>

1079
01:08:18,307 --> 01:08:20,477
<font color="#FFFFFF">But it involves us in a deadly danger.</font>

1080
01:08:20,559 --> 01:08:22,189
<font color="#FFFFFF">The deadly danger here</font>

1081
01:08:22,269 --> 01:08:26,689
<font color="#FFFFFF">is this romantic fantasy
of fighting to the end.</font>

1082
01:08:28,442 --> 01:08:29,902
<font color="#FFFFFF">What is the end,</font>

1083
01:08:30,319 --> 01:08:33,199
<font color="#FFFFFF">if not the destruction of all things?</font>

1084
01:08:34,114 --> 01:08:35,284
<font color="#FFFFFF">There's nothing heroic</font>

1085
01:08:35,365 --> 01:08:37,575
<font color="#FFFFFF">in going down fighting
if it can be avoided.</font>

1086
01:08:37,659 --> 01:08:41,119
<font color="#FFFFFF">Nothing even remotely patriotic
in death or glory</font>

1087
01:08:41,205 --> 01:08:43,335
<font color="#FFFFFF">if the odds are firmly on the former.</font>

1088
01:08:43,415 --> 01:08:46,785
<font color="#FFFFFF">Nothing inglorious
in trying to shorten a war</font>

1089
01:08:46,877 --> 01:08:48,287
<font color="#FFFFFF">that we are clearly losing.</font>

1090
01:08:48,378 --> 01:08:50,918
<font color="#FFFFFF">Losing? Europe is still...</font>

1091
01:08:51,006 --> 01:08:52,376
<font color="#FFFFFF">Europe is lost.</font>

1092
01:08:59,515 --> 01:09:02,895
<font color="#FFFFFF">And before our forces
are wiped out completely,</font>

1093
01:09:03,560 --> 01:09:05,560
<font color="#FFFFFF">now is the time to negotiate,</font>

1094
01:09:05,646 --> 01:09:08,566
<font color="#FFFFFF">in order to obtain
the best conditions possible.</font>

1095
01:09:10,567 --> 01:09:12,737
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hitler will not insist on
outrageous terms.</font>

1096
01:09:12,819 --> 01:09:14,109
<font color="#FFFFFF">He will know his own weaknesses.</font>

1097
01:09:14,196 --> 01:09:15,696
<font color="#FFFFFF">He will be reasonable.</font>

1098
01:09:15,781 --> 01:09:17,911
<font color="#FFFFFF">When will the lesson be learned?</font>

1099
01:09:18,283 --> 01:09:20,743
<font color="#FFFFFF">When will the lesson be learned?</font>

1100
01:09:22,162 --> 01:09:24,462
<font color="#FFFFFF">How many more dictators</font>

1101
01:09:24,540 --> 01:09:28,000
<font color="#FFFFFF">must be, wooed, appeased,</font>

1102
01:09:28,085 --> 01:09:30,055
<font color="#FFFFFF">good god, given immense privileges</font>

1103
01:09:30,128 --> 01:09:32,008
<font color="#FFFFFF">before we learn?</font>

1104
01:09:32,381 --> 01:09:35,381
<font color="#FFFFFF">You cannot reason with a tiger</font>

1105
01:09:35,467 --> 01:09:38,007
<font color="#FFFFFF">when your head is in its mouth!</font>

1106
01:09:39,680 --> 01:09:41,010
<font color="#FFFFFF">Prime minister.</font>

1107
01:09:42,099 --> 01:09:44,099
<font color="#FFFFFF">Winston. Winston.</font>

1108
01:09:45,394 --> 01:09:46,604
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yesterday, you gave permission...</font>

1109
01:09:46,687 --> 01:09:48,057
<font color="#FFFFFF">What permission?</font>

1110
01:09:48,146 --> 01:09:49,936
<font color="#FFFFFF">For me to meet bastianini.</font>

1111
01:09:50,023 --> 01:09:51,693
<font color="#FFFFFF">I sanctioned
the theoretical exploration...</font>

1112
01:09:51,775 --> 01:09:52,775
<font color="#FFFFFF">Theoretical?</font>

1113
01:09:52,860 --> 01:09:55,110
<font color="#FFFFFF">of what price Italy would ask.
Nothing more.</font>

1114
01:09:55,195 --> 01:09:57,155
<font color="#FFFFFF">- I did not sanction any...
- If you will not permit</font>

1115
01:09:57,239 --> 01:09:59,159
<font color="#FFFFFF">further exploration of a peace agreement,</font>

1116
01:09:59,241 --> 01:10:00,701
<font color="#FFFFFF">then you will have my resignation.</font>

1117
01:10:00,784 --> 01:10:02,414
<font color="#FFFFFF">Don't be absurd, Edward.</font>

1118
01:10:02,494 --> 01:10:05,834
<font color="#FFFFFF">- I need you. You know I do.
- I will not stand by</font>

1119
01:10:05,914 --> 01:10:09,174
<font color="#FFFFFF">to watch another generation
of young men die</font>

1120
01:10:09,251 --> 01:10:10,881
<font color="#FFFFFF">at the bloody altar of your hubris.</font>

1121
01:10:10,961 --> 01:10:13,591
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, and you would have us die as lambs!</font>

1122
01:10:13,672 --> 01:10:15,222
<font color="#FFFFFF">Was gallipoli not enough for you?</font>

1123
01:10:15,299 --> 01:10:16,799
<font color="#FFFFFF">How dare you!</font>

1124
01:10:17,217 --> 01:10:21,007
<font color="#FFFFFF">Our troops were chewing
barbed wire in flanders,</font>

1125
01:10:21,096 --> 01:10:22,506
<font color="#FFFFFF">and I saw it!</font>

1126
01:10:23,348 --> 01:10:26,728
<font color="#FFFFFF">Opening a second front,
outflanking the turks</font>

1127
01:10:26,810 --> 01:10:29,190
<font color="#FFFFFF">was a serious military idea,</font>

1128
01:10:29,271 --> 01:10:31,231
<font color="#FFFFFF">and it could have
damn well worked if the...</font>

1129
01:10:31,315 --> 01:10:33,275
<font color="#FFFFFF">If the admirals and the first sea lord</font>

1130
01:10:33,358 --> 01:10:36,438
<font color="#FFFFFF">hadn't dithered away
our element of surprise.</font>

1131
01:10:40,908 --> 01:10:42,368
<font color="#FFFFFF">Choice is yours, Winston.</font>

1132
01:10:42,826 --> 01:10:45,036
<font color="#FFFFFF">You have 24 hours
to enter into peace talks,</font>

1133
01:10:45,120 --> 01:10:46,410
<font color="#FFFFFF">or I shall resign.</font>

1134
01:11:01,094 --> 01:11:02,434
<font color="#FFFFFF">I told him.</font>

1135
01:11:02,888 --> 01:11:04,348
<font color="#FFFFFF">It shook him.</font>

1136
01:11:05,140 --> 01:11:06,520
<font color="#FFFFFF">I imagine it did.</font>

1137
01:11:06,600 --> 01:11:08,480
<font color="#FFFFFF">Gave him 24 hours.</font>

1138
01:11:08,560 --> 01:11:11,650
<font color="#FFFFFF">I don't expect he'll agree,
so I shall resign first.</font>

1139
01:11:11,730 --> 01:11:13,690
<font color="#FFFFFF">You then follow, that's critical if we're</font>

1140
01:11:13,774 --> 01:11:15,864
<font color="#FFFFFF">to trigger a vote
of no confidence in the house.</font>

1141
01:11:16,360 --> 01:11:17,740
<font color="#FFFFFF">I shall announce it.</font>

1142
01:11:19,696 --> 01:11:21,196
<font color="#FFFFFF">The king will back us.</font>

1143
01:11:37,589 --> 01:11:38,879
<font color="#FFFFFF">Prime minister.</font>

1144
01:11:38,966 --> 01:11:40,336
<font color="#FFFFFF">I wonder if we might schedule you</font>

1145
01:11:40,425 --> 01:11:41,585
<font color="#FFFFFF">to address the outer cabinet.</font>

1146
01:11:43,762 --> 01:11:45,312
<font color="#FFFFFF">Today, the admiralty</font>

1147
01:11:45,389 --> 01:11:47,519
<font color="#FFFFFF">have made an order requesting all owners</font>

1148
01:11:47,599 --> 01:11:49,019
<font color="#FFFFFF">of self-propelled pleasure craft</font>

1149
01:11:49,101 --> 01:11:51,691
<font color="#FFFFFF">between 30 and 100 feet in length</font>

1150
01:11:51,770 --> 01:11:55,020
<font color="#FFFFFF">to send all particulars
to the admiralty immediately...</font>

1151
01:11:55,107 --> 01:11:57,107
<font color="#FFFFFF">To brigadier Nicholson.</font>

1152
01:12:00,237 --> 01:12:04,367
<font color="#FFFFFF">30 infantry brigade, calais.</font>

1153
01:12:07,411 --> 01:12:08,831
<font color="#FFFFFF">Every hour</font>

1154
01:12:09,872 --> 01:12:12,172
<font color="#FFFFFF">you continue to exist</font>

1155
01:12:13,375 --> 01:12:15,415
<font color="#FFFFFF">is of the greatest help</font>

1156
01:12:16,420 --> 01:12:19,010
<font color="#FFFFFF">to our forces at dunkirk.</font>

1157
01:12:22,009 --> 01:12:26,719
<font color="#FFFFFF">Have the greatest possible admiration</font>

1158
01:12:27,681 --> 01:12:29,681
<font color="#FFFFFF">for your splendid stand.</font>

1159
01:12:35,022 --> 01:12:37,112
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your evacuation, however,</font>

1160
01:12:37,858 --> 01:12:40,398
<font color="#FFFFFF">will not take place.</font>

1161
01:12:46,158 --> 01:12:47,738
<font color="#FFFFFF">I repeat,</font>

1162
01:12:49,870 --> 01:12:51,790
<font color="#FFFFFF">will not take place.</font>

1163
01:13:00,255 --> 01:13:01,375
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sign.</font>

1164
01:13:16,688 --> 01:13:18,728
<font color="#FFFFFF">Here. Here.</font>

1165
01:13:22,277 --> 01:13:23,647
<font color="#FFFFFF">May I be excused?</font>

1166
01:13:24,029 --> 01:13:25,199
<font color="#FFFFFF">You may not.</font>

1167
01:13:27,157 --> 01:13:28,947
<font color="#FFFFFF">What is this about?</font>

1168
01:13:31,537 --> 01:13:33,197
<font color="#FFFFFF">No one tells us anything.</font>

1169
01:13:35,082 --> 01:13:36,922
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's all classified.</font>

1170
01:13:38,669 --> 01:13:41,669
<font color="#FFFFFF">We hear scraps,
and it's worse than knowing nothing.</font>

1171
01:13:46,468 --> 01:13:48,218
<font color="#FFFFFF">What would you like to know?</font>

1172
01:13:56,019 --> 01:13:58,479
<font color="#FFFFFF">How many men will survive?</font>

1173
01:14:05,445 --> 01:14:06,735
<font color="#FFFFFF">Come with me.</font>

1174
01:14:15,205 --> 01:14:16,785
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm not allowed in the map room.</font>

1175
01:14:16,874 --> 01:14:18,424
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Well, you are now.
- Prime minister.</font>

1176
01:14:18,500 --> 01:14:21,090
<font color="#FFFFFF">At ease, gentlemen.</font>

1177
01:14:22,796 --> 01:14:24,006
<font color="#FFFFFF">Now...</font>

1178
01:14:27,301 --> 01:14:29,841
<font color="#FFFFFF">The German army controls every French port</font>

1179
01:14:29,928 --> 01:14:32,388
<font color="#FFFFFF">except dunkirk here
and calais here to the west,</font>

1180
01:14:32,472 --> 01:14:35,062
<font color="#FFFFFF">where the Garrison
under brigadier Nicholson</font>

1181
01:14:35,142 --> 01:14:39,272
<font color="#FFFFFF">is drawing fire and delaying
the German advance on dunkirk.</font>

1182
01:14:39,354 --> 01:14:42,944
<font color="#FFFFFF">At both points, our troops are encircled.</font>

1183
01:14:43,025 --> 01:14:45,035
<font color="#FFFFFF">Now, we are still trying</font>

1184
01:14:45,110 --> 01:14:47,610
<font color="#FFFFFF">to clear dunkirk harbor of wrecked ships</font>

1185
01:14:47,696 --> 01:14:50,486
<font color="#FFFFFF">so that we can then land
the boats we need to get</font>

1186
01:14:50,574 --> 01:14:52,034
<font color="#FFFFFF">our boys off those beaches.</font>

1187
01:14:52,117 --> 01:14:54,987
<font color="#FFFFFF">But enemy aircraft
is attacking us constantly.</font>

1188
01:14:55,078 --> 01:14:59,668
<font color="#FFFFFF">Our only hope in dunkirk
is thick cloud cover</font>

1189
01:14:59,917 --> 01:15:02,997
<font color="#FFFFFF">to thwart these attacks,
but the skies remain clear.</font>

1190
01:15:03,587 --> 01:15:07,837
<font color="#FFFFFF">And even then, I am told
we will need a...</font>

1191
01:15:07,925 --> 01:15:11,395
<font color="#FFFFFF">A miracle to get even
ten percent of our men out.</font>

1192
01:15:14,515 --> 01:15:16,895
<font color="#FFFFFF">Courage, miss Layton.</font>

1193
01:15:18,018 --> 01:15:19,308
<font color="#FFFFFF">Courage.</font>

1194
01:15:19,937 --> 01:15:21,187
<font color="#FFFFFF">General.</font>

1195
01:15:21,647 --> 01:15:23,937
<font color="#FFFFFF">How long have they got</font>

1196
01:15:25,275 --> 01:15:26,815
<font color="#FFFFFF">if we don't rescue them?</font>

1197
01:15:29,947 --> 01:15:32,657
<font color="#FFFFFF">One, maybe</font>

1198
01:15:33,784 --> 01:15:35,294
<font color="#FFFFFF">two days.</font>

1199
01:15:40,916 --> 01:15:43,496
<font color="#FFFFFF">News from calais, the 30th infantry, sir.</font>

1200
01:15:43,585 --> 01:15:45,455
<font color="#FFFFFF">They've retreated to the town's citadel</font>

1201
01:15:45,546 --> 01:15:48,166
<font color="#FFFFFF">as a last and probably hopeless stand.</font>

1202
01:15:48,257 --> 01:15:50,927
<font color="#FFFFFF">The order, "every man
for himself," has been given.</font>

1203
01:15:51,009 --> 01:15:52,389
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Thank you, thank you.
- Brigadier Nicholson.</font>

1204
01:15:52,469 --> 01:15:54,389
<font color="#FFFFFF">- There's a telegram, sir.
- Thank you.</font>

1205
01:15:59,685 --> 01:16:00,855
<font color="#FFFFFF">Good show, chaps.</font>

1206
01:16:00,936 --> 01:16:03,396
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well done, lads. Well done.</font>

1207
01:16:03,480 --> 01:16:04,980
<font color="#FFFFFF">All right.</font>

1208
01:16:08,610 --> 01:16:10,400
<font color="#FFFFFF">He's losing too much blood.</font>

1209
01:16:10,487 --> 01:16:12,697
<font color="#FFFFFF">We need another transfusion here.</font>

1210
01:16:18,120 --> 01:16:20,040
<font color="#FFFFFF">All right, men? All right?</font>

1211
01:16:33,051 --> 01:16:35,641
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your evacuation, however,</font>

1212
01:16:36,054 --> 01:16:38,604
<font color="#FFFFFF">will not take place.</font>

1213
01:16:40,517 --> 01:16:43,767
<font color="#FFFFFF">I repeat, will not take place.</font>

1214
01:17:30,817 --> 01:17:32,397
<font color="#FFFFFF">Go to bed, pig.</font>

1215
01:17:34,238 --> 01:17:35,948
<font color="#FFFFFF">You must sleep.</font>

1216
01:17:38,492 --> 01:17:40,452
<font color="#FFFFFF">Leave me, clemmie.</font>

1217
01:17:41,119 --> 01:17:43,999
<font color="#FFFFFF">The opportunity for doing so
passed a long time ago.</font>

1218
01:18:15,571 --> 01:18:17,491
<font color="#FFFFFF">Operator.
How may I direct your call?</font>

1219
01:18:17,573 --> 01:18:20,623
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Give me ramsay.
- One moment, please.</font>

1220
01:18:21,994 --> 01:18:23,874
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Bertie?
- Sir?</font>

1221
01:18:24,079 --> 01:18:25,409
<font color="#FFFFFF">What's been the response?</font>

1222
01:18:25,497 --> 01:18:26,917
<font color="#FFFFFF">It will take time.</font>

1223
01:18:26,999 --> 01:18:28,289
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's too soon to judge.</font>

1224
01:18:28,375 --> 01:18:29,825
<font color="#FFFFFF">How many boats so far?</font>

1225
01:18:29,918 --> 01:18:31,878
<font color="#FFFFFF">Winston, it will take time.</font>

1226
01:18:31,962 --> 01:18:35,512
<font color="#FFFFFF">The request for civilian boats,
bertie, was not a request.</font>

1227
01:18:35,591 --> 01:18:37,631
<font color="#FFFFFF">It was an order!</font>

1228
01:18:52,566 --> 01:18:54,606
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Miss Layton.
- Sir.</font>

1229
01:18:54,693 --> 01:18:57,493
<font color="#FFFFFF">I need to reach,</font>

1230
01:18:57,946 --> 01:18:59,106
<font color="#FFFFFF">to reach,</font>

1231
01:19:00,282 --> 01:19:01,702
<font color="#FFFFFF">to speak to...</font>

1232
01:19:03,160 --> 01:19:04,200
<font color="#FFFFFF">To?</font>

1233
01:19:04,912 --> 01:19:06,042
<font color="#FFFFFF">3:00 P.M.</font>

1234
01:19:06,121 --> 01:19:07,371
<font color="#FFFFFF">2:00 P.M., sir?</font>

1235
01:19:08,415 --> 01:19:10,035
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes. Yes.</font>

1236
01:19:10,125 --> 01:19:12,995
<font color="#FFFFFF">Ask Bridges to summon the...</font>

1237
01:19:14,087 --> 01:19:15,167
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, god.</font>

1238
01:19:15,255 --> 01:19:17,585
<font color="#FFFFFF">The war cabinet, at 3:00 P.M.</font>

1239
01:19:17,674 --> 01:19:18,804
<font color="#FFFFFF">Thank you!</font>

1240
01:19:22,971 --> 01:19:24,141
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sir.</font>

1241
01:19:24,723 --> 01:19:27,433
<font color="#FFFFFF">From lord gort in France, sir.</font>

1242
01:19:32,356 --> 01:19:34,566
<font color="#FFFFFF">Belgium has fallen.</font>

1243
01:19:36,527 --> 01:19:39,697
<font color="#FFFFFF">They will surrender at midnight.</font>

1244
01:19:42,616 --> 01:19:44,616
<font color="#FFFFFF">France will soon follow suit.</font>

1245
01:19:57,631 --> 01:19:58,971
<font color="#FFFFFF">We have received reports</font>

1246
01:19:59,049 --> 01:20:00,759
<font color="#FFFFFF">that the most probable method of attack</font>

1247
01:20:00,843 --> 01:20:03,053
<font color="#FFFFFF">which Germany might employ
against this country</font>

1248
01:20:03,178 --> 01:20:05,928
<font color="#FFFFFF">is a large fleet of fast motorboats,</font>

1249
01:20:06,014 --> 01:20:08,774
<font color="#FFFFFF">possibly up to 200,
carrying a hundred men apiece,</font>

1250
01:20:08,851 --> 01:20:11,601
<font color="#FFFFFF">to carry out a seaborne raid
on a large scale.</font>

1251
01:20:11,687 --> 01:20:14,267
<font color="#FFFFFF">By these means,
a considerable force of the enemy</font>

1252
01:20:14,356 --> 01:20:16,396
<font color="#FFFFFF">could be landed
at many points on the coast</font>

1253
01:20:16,483 --> 01:20:19,613
<font color="#FFFFFF">simultaneously with airborne raids inland.</font>

1254
01:20:19,695 --> 01:20:23,455
<font color="#FFFFFF">We do not feel
that by naval or air action,</font>

1255
01:20:23,532 --> 01:20:25,532
<font color="#FFFFFF">we could prevent such a landing.</font>

1256
01:20:28,120 --> 01:20:29,540
<font color="#FFFFFF">Could you repeat that?</font>

1257
01:20:29,955 --> 01:20:31,295
<font color="#FFFFFF">We must prepare</font>

1258
01:20:31,373 --> 01:20:33,503
<font color="#FFFFFF">for the imminent invasion of our island.</font>

1259
01:20:37,588 --> 01:20:40,088
<font color="#FFFFFF">We must prepare for
the imminent invasion of our island.</font>

1260
01:20:40,841 --> 01:20:42,551
<font color="#FFFFFF">We recommend that the country</font>

1261
01:20:42,634 --> 01:20:45,604
<font color="#FFFFFF">should be warned and roused
to the immediate danger,</font>

1262
01:20:45,679 --> 01:20:47,139
<font color="#FFFFFF">and that all personnel</font>

1263
01:20:47,222 --> 01:20:49,892
<font color="#FFFFFF">required to put britain
in a state of defense</font>

1264
01:20:49,975 --> 01:20:53,275
<font color="#FFFFFF">should be mobilized
without a moment's delay.</font>

1265
01:20:53,353 --> 01:20:54,523
<font color="#FFFFFF">Lights.</font>

1266
01:21:00,611 --> 01:21:03,321
<font color="#FFFFFF">Thank you, general.</font>

1267
01:21:06,200 --> 01:21:10,200
<font color="#FFFFFF">Let all preparations be made.</font>

1268
01:21:11,705 --> 01:21:13,615
<font color="#FFFFFF">Let the record state, I have received word</font>

1269
01:21:13,707 --> 01:21:15,377
<font color="#FFFFFF">from the Italian embassy in London.</font>

1270
01:21:15,459 --> 01:21:17,629
<font color="#FFFFFF">Italy is prepared to mediate a resolution</font>

1271
01:21:17,711 --> 01:21:19,841
<font color="#FFFFFF">between britain, its allies and Germany.</font>

1272
01:21:25,928 --> 01:21:28,468
<font color="#FFFFFF">Perhaps then,</font>

1273
01:21:30,307 --> 01:21:35,057
<font color="#FFFFFF">the time for such an offer from us</font>

1274
01:21:35,145 --> 01:21:36,765
<font color="#FFFFFF">is when...</font>

1275
01:21:41,318 --> 01:21:43,358
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, is when...</font>

1276
01:21:45,739 --> 01:21:51,119
<font color="#FFFFFF">Is when Germany has made
an unsuccessful attempt</font>

1277
01:21:51,203 --> 01:21:53,793
<font color="#FFFFFF">- to invade this country.
- Unsuccessful?</font>

1278
01:21:53,872 --> 01:21:55,792
<font color="#FFFFFF">Then you leave me
no other option but to offer...</font>

1279
01:21:55,874 --> 01:21:57,634
<font color="#FFFFFF">Winston. Winston!</font>

1280
01:21:58,293 --> 01:22:02,463
<font color="#FFFFFF">You are refusing to grasp the realities</font>

1281
01:22:02,548 --> 01:22:05,968
<font color="#FFFFFF">of how precarious our position is.</font>

1282
01:22:06,677 --> 01:22:10,507
<font color="#FFFFFF">Our entire army is about to be wiped out.</font>

1283
01:22:10,889 --> 01:22:13,729
<font color="#FFFFFF">Terms must be struck.</font>

1284
01:22:18,730 --> 01:22:20,070
<font color="#FFFFFF">Anthony.</font>

1285
01:22:38,458 --> 01:22:41,038
<font color="#FFFFFF">Then it seems we...</font>

1286
01:22:43,005 --> 01:22:45,055
<font color="#FFFFFF">We have no choice</font>

1287
01:22:46,008 --> 01:22:48,638
<font color="#FFFFFF">but to at least consider the</font>

1288
01:22:49,386 --> 01:22:52,506
<font color="#FFFFFF">path of negotiation.</font>

1289
01:22:54,516 --> 01:22:57,556
<font color="#FFFFFF">If Hitler's peace terms are</font>

1290
01:22:59,688 --> 01:23:03,438
<font color="#FFFFFF">over lordship of central Europe,</font>

1291
01:23:04,276 --> 01:23:08,276
<font color="#FFFFFF">return of certain German colonies,</font>

1292
01:23:09,323 --> 01:23:13,373
<font color="#FFFFFF">and if he will leave us</font>

1293
01:23:14,578 --> 01:23:16,868
<font color="#FFFFFF">our independence,</font>

1294
01:23:19,166 --> 01:23:22,336
<font color="#FFFFFF">then I'd be grateful</font>

1295
01:23:23,337 --> 01:23:26,007
<font color="#FFFFFF">to get out of our present...</font>

1296
01:23:27,508 --> 01:23:28,878
<font color="#FFFFFF">Difficulties.</font>

1297
01:23:30,511 --> 01:23:32,301
<font color="#FFFFFF">But it is unlikely</font>

1298
01:23:33,263 --> 01:23:36,103
<font color="#FFFFFF">that he will make such an offer.</font>

1299
01:23:36,183 --> 01:23:41,353
<font color="#FFFFFF">But if I were told
what the German terms were,</font>

1300
01:23:46,068 --> 01:23:50,238
<font color="#FFFFFF">well, then I'd be prepared
to consider them.</font>

1301
01:23:51,990 --> 01:23:54,200
<font color="#FFFFFF">Thank you, prime minister.</font>

1302
01:23:55,035 --> 01:23:57,575
<font color="#FFFFFF">We shall prepare
a draft memorandum at once.</font>

1303
01:24:10,133 --> 01:24:14,053
<font color="#FFFFFF">I have come to wonder,</font>

1304
01:24:14,137 --> 01:24:16,967
<font color="#FFFFFF">in recent days...</font>

1305
01:24:21,728 --> 01:24:24,188
<font color="#FFFFFF">Whether it was...</font>

1306
01:24:27,025 --> 01:24:28,895
<font color="#FFFFFF">Part of my duty...</font>

1307
01:24:32,406 --> 01:24:35,156
<font color="#FFFFFF">Part of my...</font>

1308
01:24:36,034 --> 01:24:38,504
<font color="#FFFFFF">Part of my duty to...</font>

1309
01:24:40,163 --> 01:24:42,293
<font color="#FFFFFF">To consider...</font>

1310
01:24:44,251 --> 01:24:45,841
<font color="#FFFFFF">To consider,</font>

1311
01:24:52,217 --> 01:24:54,387
<font color="#FFFFFF">to consider...</font>

1312
01:24:56,972 --> 01:24:59,472
<font color="#FFFFFF">whether it was...</font>

1313
01:24:59,558 --> 01:25:01,848
<font color="#FFFFFF">Will that be all for tonight, sir?</font>

1314
01:25:06,231 --> 01:25:09,281
<font color="#FFFFFF">whether it was part of my duty</font>

1315
01:25:09,359 --> 01:25:13,449
<font color="#FFFFFF">entering into...</font>

1316
01:25:14,364 --> 01:25:17,534
<font color="#FFFFFF">Into negotiations with,</font>

1317
01:25:22,331 --> 01:25:23,711
<font color="#FFFFFF">that...</font>

1318
01:25:25,959 --> 01:25:27,839
<font color="#FFFFFF">that corporal...</font>

1319
01:25:33,800 --> 01:25:35,680
<font color="#FFFFFF">That child.</font>

1320
01:25:40,098 --> 01:25:43,018
<font color="#FFFFFF">And monster of wickedness.</font>

1321
01:25:44,770 --> 01:25:45,940
<font color="#FFFFFF">That butcher.</font>

1322
01:25:46,146 --> 01:25:49,516
<font color="#FFFFFF">That savage.</font>

1323
01:25:49,858 --> 01:25:52,148
<font color="#FFFFFF">Monstrous savage.</font>

1324
01:25:58,909 --> 01:26:00,739
<font color="#FFFFFF">That wicked</font>

1325
01:26:01,870 --> 01:26:04,080
<font color="#FFFFFF">house painter.</font>

1326
01:26:07,292 --> 01:26:09,212
<font color="#FFFFFF">House painter!</font>

1327
01:26:16,176 --> 01:26:19,296
<font color="#FFFFFF">Where were we?</font>

1328
01:26:22,766 --> 01:26:23,976
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well?</font>

1329
01:26:26,854 --> 01:26:28,774
<font color="#FFFFFF">I didn't understand you, sir.</font>

1330
01:26:30,315 --> 01:26:31,725
<font color="#FFFFFF">You were...</font>

1331
01:26:32,109 --> 01:26:33,359
<font color="#FFFFFF">Were?</font>

1332
01:26:34,444 --> 01:26:35,744
<font color="#FFFFFF">You were mumbling.</font>

1333
01:26:35,821 --> 01:26:37,571
<font color="#FFFFFF">"Mumbling."</font>

1334
01:26:42,828 --> 01:26:45,748
<font color="#FFFFFF">The right words</font>

1335
01:26:47,291 --> 01:26:48,751
<font color="#FFFFFF">won't come.</font>

1336
01:26:49,376 --> 01:26:50,586
<font color="#FFFFFF">They will come, sir.</font>

1337
01:26:51,253 --> 01:26:53,843
<font color="#FFFFFF">No one can put words together like you.</font>

1338
01:27:04,725 --> 01:27:05,735
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh!</font>

1339
01:27:16,820 --> 01:27:18,320
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your Beau?</font>

1340
01:27:19,698 --> 01:27:21,028
<font color="#FFFFFF">My brother.</font>

1341
01:27:23,744 --> 01:27:25,204
<font color="#FFFFFF">Where is he now?</font>

1342
01:27:25,871 --> 01:27:27,831
<font color="#FFFFFF">He was falling back on dunkirk.</font>

1343
01:27:29,458 --> 01:27:31,128
<font color="#FFFFFF">But he never made it.</font>

1344
01:27:55,776 --> 01:27:56,936
<font color="#FFFFFF">What?</font>

1345
01:28:02,533 --> 01:28:04,453
<font color="#FFFFFF">Just looking at you.</font>

1346
01:28:31,395 --> 01:28:33,155
<font color="#FFFFFF">Shall I read back what we have?</font>

1347
01:28:35,691 --> 01:28:37,861
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes, please.</font>

1348
01:28:43,740 --> 01:28:46,790
<font color="#FFFFFF">"I have come to wonder in recent days</font>

1349
01:28:47,703 --> 01:28:50,083
<font color="#FFFFFF">"whether it was my duty to consider</font>

1350
01:28:50,163 --> 01:28:54,633
<font color="#FFFFFF">"entering into negotiations with..."</font>

1351
01:28:58,338 --> 01:28:59,758
<font color="#FFFFFF">With?</font>

1352
01:29:47,930 --> 01:29:49,970
<font color="#FFFFFF">I've just been standing,</font>

1353
01:29:50,265 --> 01:29:54,225
<font color="#FFFFFF">imagining never being here anymore,</font>

1354
01:29:55,312 --> 01:29:57,732
<font color="#FFFFFF">whether it is because I'm no longer alive</font>

1355
01:29:57,814 --> 01:30:00,154
<font color="#FFFFFF">or that the palace itself is gone.</font>

1356
01:30:00,234 --> 01:30:02,034
<font color="#FFFFFF">Canada.</font>

1357
01:30:03,237 --> 01:30:04,647
<font color="#FFFFFF">You must decide, sir.</font>

1358
01:30:05,322 --> 01:30:06,492
<font color="#FFFFFF">You could rule in exile.</font>

1359
01:30:06,573 --> 01:30:09,083
<font color="#FFFFFF">Truly? Is that to be my fate?</font>

1360
01:30:14,122 --> 01:30:15,502
<font color="#FFFFFF">You know something?</font>

1361
01:30:15,582 --> 01:30:18,962
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm aware in this moment of feeling angry.</font>

1362
01:30:21,630 --> 01:30:23,260
<font color="#FFFFFF">Bloody angry.</font>

1363
01:30:26,927 --> 01:30:28,637
<font color="#FFFFFF">Darling.</font>

1364
01:30:31,640 --> 01:30:33,390
<font color="#FFFFFF">Winston, darling.</font>

1365
01:30:36,186 --> 01:30:37,766
<font color="#FFFFFF">There's someone to see you.</font>

1366
01:30:38,438 --> 01:30:39,768
<font color="#FFFFFF">You have a visitor.</font>

1367
01:30:51,118 --> 01:30:53,408
<font color="#FFFFFF">My darling, you have the full weight</font>

1368
01:30:53,495 --> 01:30:55,115
<font color="#FFFFFF">of the world on your shoulders.</font>

1369
01:30:55,789 --> 01:30:57,619
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, I know, I know.</font>

1370
01:30:57,708 --> 01:31:00,168
<font color="#FFFFFF">But these inner battles</font>

1371
01:31:01,712 --> 01:31:04,212
<font color="#FFFFFF">have actually trained you</font>

1372
01:31:04,756 --> 01:31:06,166
<font color="#FFFFFF">for this very moment.</font>

1373
01:31:07,050 --> 01:31:09,720
<font color="#FFFFFF">You are strong because you are imperfect.</font>

1374
01:31:09,803 --> 01:31:13,853
<font color="#FFFFFF">You are wise because you have doubts.</font>

1375
01:31:16,101 --> 01:31:18,521
<font color="#FFFFFF">Now, shall I let him in?</font>

1376
01:31:20,272 --> 01:31:21,482
<font color="#FFFFFF">Who?</font>

1377
01:31:22,524 --> 01:31:23,694
<font color="#FFFFFF">The king.</font>

1378
01:31:23,775 --> 01:31:25,815
<font color="#FFFFFF">Which king?</font>

1379
01:31:26,528 --> 01:31:28,358
<font color="#FFFFFF">Our king?</font>

1380
01:31:28,447 --> 01:31:31,657
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, if it isn't him,
it's a marvelous impersonation.</font>

1381
01:31:41,376 --> 01:31:42,836
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mr. Churchill.</font>

1382
01:31:43,128 --> 01:31:46,628
<font color="#FFFFFF">I hope you can forgive the late hour, but</font>

1383
01:31:46,715 --> 01:31:50,175
<font color="#FFFFFF">your wife thought tonight
would be a good time.</font>

1384
01:31:51,637 --> 01:31:52,847
<font color="#FFFFFF">Shall we sit?</font>

1385
01:31:53,263 --> 01:31:54,643
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, yes.</font>

1386
01:31:54,723 --> 01:31:56,523
<font color="#FFFFFF">Please.</font>

1387
01:32:00,729 --> 01:32:02,399
<font color="#FFFFFF">Something to drink, perhaps?</font>

1388
01:32:02,481 --> 01:32:03,611
<font color="#FFFFFF">No.</font>

1389
01:32:10,781 --> 01:32:16,161
<font color="#FFFFFF">I received a visit.</font>

1390
01:32:17,204 --> 01:32:18,464
<font color="#FFFFFF">From?</font>

1391
01:32:18,539 --> 01:32:20,039
<font color="#FFFFFF">Viscount halifax.</font>

1392
01:32:20,123 --> 01:32:23,003
<font color="#FFFFFF">It appears that
the prospect of a peace deal</font>

1393
01:32:24,378 --> 01:32:27,838
<font color="#FFFFFF">has increased dramatically.</font>

1394
01:32:29,508 --> 01:32:33,928
<font color="#FFFFFF">The war cabinet is drafting
a letter to Mussolini,</font>

1395
01:32:34,638 --> 01:32:39,808
<font color="#FFFFFF">asking him to broker talks
with herr Hitler.</font>

1396
01:32:43,063 --> 01:32:46,153
<font color="#FFFFFF">Then halifax was correct.</font>

1397
01:32:48,402 --> 01:32:50,702
<font color="#FFFFFF">I should like to know your mind.</font>

1398
01:32:50,779 --> 01:32:53,779
<font color="#FFFFFF">It would be helpful to know yours first.</font>

1399
01:32:54,116 --> 01:32:57,536
<font color="#FFFFFF">I should like to know it myself.</font>

1400
01:32:59,371 --> 01:33:01,501
<font color="#FFFFFF">Nations</font>

1401
01:33:01,957 --> 01:33:05,127
<font color="#FFFFFF">which go down fighting rise again,
and those</font>

1402
01:33:06,086 --> 01:33:08,376
<font color="#FFFFFF">that surrender tamely are finished.</font>

1403
01:33:08,463 --> 01:33:09,713
<font color="#FFFFFF">Belgium?</font>

1404
01:33:10,674 --> 01:33:12,094
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Collapsed.
- Norway?</font>

1405
01:33:12,176 --> 01:33:13,506
<font color="#FFFFFF">Holland.</font>

1406
01:33:14,094 --> 01:33:15,724
<font color="#FFFFFF">France any hour.</font>

1407
01:33:15,804 --> 01:33:17,224
<font color="#FFFFFF">And the mood of parliament?</font>

1408
01:33:17,306 --> 01:33:18,386
<font color="#FFFFFF">Fear. Panic.</font>

1409
01:33:18,473 --> 01:33:20,023
<font color="#FFFFFF">And you?</font>

1410
01:33:21,560 --> 01:33:23,480
<font color="#FFFFFF">Are you not afraid?</font>

1411
01:33:24,855 --> 01:33:27,905
<font color="#FFFFFF">I am, most terribly.</font>

1412
01:33:29,568 --> 01:33:34,318
<font color="#FFFFFF">Support in the war cabinet</font>

1413
01:33:35,490 --> 01:33:37,700
<font color="#FFFFFF">for the campaign of resistance</font>

1414
01:33:39,077 --> 01:33:40,287
<font color="#FFFFFF">has collapsed.</font>

1415
01:33:48,462 --> 01:33:53,972
<font color="#FFFFFF">Later today,
I will address the house accordingly.</font>

1416
01:34:04,770 --> 01:34:06,600
<font color="#FFFFFF">You have my support.</font>

1417
01:34:13,904 --> 01:34:15,494
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your majesty?</font>

1418
01:34:16,532 --> 01:34:18,662
<font color="#FFFFFF">You have my support.</font>

1419
01:34:21,078 --> 01:34:22,618
<font color="#FFFFFF">I confess, I</font>

1420
01:34:23,497 --> 01:34:27,417
<font color="#FFFFFF">had some reservations about you
at first, but</font>

1421
01:34:27,501 --> 01:34:31,051
<font color="#FFFFFF">while some in this country
dreaded your appointment,</font>

1422
01:34:31,129 --> 01:34:35,259
<font color="#FFFFFF">none, none dreaded it like Adolf Hitler.</font>

1423
01:34:35,342 --> 01:34:39,142
<font color="#FFFFFF">Whomever can strike fear
into that brute heart</font>

1424
01:34:39,680 --> 01:34:42,220
<font color="#FFFFFF">is worthy of all of our trust.</font>

1425
01:34:42,724 --> 01:34:44,024
<font color="#FFFFFF">We shall work together.</font>

1426
01:34:44,101 --> 01:34:46,981
<font color="#FFFFFF">You shall have my support at any hour.</font>

1427
01:34:47,646 --> 01:34:49,266
<font color="#FFFFFF">Beat the buggers.</font>

1428
01:34:50,691 --> 01:34:52,361
<font color="#FFFFFF">I will go to parliament.</font>

1429
01:34:53,277 --> 01:34:56,447
<font color="#FFFFFF">But without support in my own party,</font>

1430
01:34:57,030 --> 01:34:58,910
<font color="#FFFFFF">I must sue for peace.</font>

1431
01:35:02,953 --> 01:35:04,413
<font color="#FFFFFF">You once gave me some advice.</font>

1432
01:35:04,496 --> 01:35:06,916
<font color="#FFFFFF">Perhaps I can... I can give you some.</font>

1433
01:35:08,167 --> 01:35:09,877
<font color="#FFFFFF">Go to the people.</font>

1434
01:35:09,960 --> 01:35:12,340
<font color="#FFFFFF">Let them instruct you.</font>

1435
01:35:12,421 --> 01:35:15,471
<font color="#FFFFFF">Quite silently, they usually do.</font>

1436
01:35:15,883 --> 01:35:17,263
<font color="#FFFFFF">But tell them</font>

1437
01:35:18,302 --> 01:35:20,972
<font color="#FFFFFF">the truth unvarnished.</font>

1438
01:35:21,054 --> 01:35:23,474
<font color="#FFFFFF">If invasion is imminent,</font>

1439
01:35:23,557 --> 01:35:25,677
<font color="#FFFFFF">if our troops in France are lost,</font>

1440
01:35:26,101 --> 01:35:27,691
<font color="#FFFFFF">they must be prepared.</font>

1441
01:35:31,148 --> 01:35:32,938
<font color="#FFFFFF">On certain matters,</font>

1442
01:35:34,902 --> 01:35:39,282
<font color="#FFFFFF">I have very few people with whom I can</font>

1443
01:35:39,698 --> 01:35:42,408
<font color="#FFFFFF">talk frankly.</font>

1444
01:35:42,492 --> 01:35:44,242
<font color="#FFFFFF">Perhaps now we have each other.</font>

1445
01:35:46,371 --> 01:35:48,791
<font color="#FFFFFF">And I no longer scare you?</font>

